\lang1033\ldblquote I reckon the staff are safer than most people while Dumble\-dore\rquote s headmaster; he\rquote s supposed to be the only one Voldemort ever feared, isn\rquote t he?\rdblquote  Harry went on.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn gazed into space for a moment or two: He seemed to be thinking over Harry\rquote s words.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, yes, it is true that He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named has never sought a fight with Dumbledore,\rdblquote  he muttered grudgingly.\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote And I suppose one could argue that as I have not joined the Death Eaters, He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named can hardly count me a friend \'85 in which case, I might well be safer a little closer to Albus. \'85 I cannot pretend that Amelia Bones\rquote s death did not shake me. \'85 If she, with all her Ministry contacts and protection \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore reentered the room and Slughorn jumped as though he had forgotten he was in the house.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, there you are, Albus,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You\rquote ve been a very long time. Upset stomach?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I was merely reading the Muggle magazines,\rdblquote  said Dum\-bledore. \ldblquote I do love knitting patterns. Well, Harry, we have tres\-passed upon Horace\rquote s hospitality quite long enough; I think it is time for us to leave.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Not at all reluctant to obey, Harry jumped to his feet. Slughorn seemed taken aback.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re leaving?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, indeed. I think I know a lost cause when I see one.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lost\'85 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn seemed agitated. He twiddled his fat thumbs and fidg\-eted as he watched Dumbledore fasten his traveling cloak, and Harry zip up his jacket.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I\rquote m sorry you don\rquote t want the job, Horace,\rdblquote  said Dumble\-dore, raising his uninjured hand in a farewell salute. \ldblquote Hogwarts would have been glad to see you back again. Our greatly increased security notwithstanding, you will always be welcome to visit, should you wish to.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes \'85 well \'85 very gracious \'85 as I say \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good-bye, then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bye,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were at the front door when there was a shout from behind them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right, all right, I\rquote ll do it!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
