\lang1033 Harry said nothing; he was thinking too hard. Narcissa Malfoy would not have let her precious son out of her sight willingly; Mal\-foy must have made a real effort to free himself from her clutches.\lang3081  \lang1033 Harry, knowing and loathing Malfoy, was sure the reason could not be innocent.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He glanced around. Mrs. Weasley and Ginny were bending over the Pygmy Puffs. Mr. Weasley was delightedly examining a pack of Muggle marked playing cards. Fred and George were both helping customers. On the other side of the glass, Hagrid was standing with his back to them, looking up and down the street.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get under here, quick,\rdblquote  said Harry, pulling his Invisibility Cloak out of his bag.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \emdash  I don\rquote t know, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking uncer\-tainly toward Mrs. Weasley.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come \i on\i0 !\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She hesitated for a second longer, then ducked under the cloak with Harry and Ron. Nobody noticed them vanish; they were all too interested in Fred and George\rquote s products. Harry, Ron, and Her\-mione squeezed their way out of the door as quickly as they could, but by the time they gained the street, Malfoy had disappeared just as successfully as they had.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He was going in that direction,\rdblquote  murmured Harry as quietly as possible, so that the humming Hagrid would not hear them. \ldblquote C\rquote mon.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They scurried along, peering left and right, through shop win\-dows and doors, until Hermione pointed ahead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s him, isn\rquote t it?\rdblquote  she whispered. \ldblquote Turning left?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Big surprise,\rdblquote  whispered Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For Malfoy had glanced around, then slid into Knockturn Alley and out of sight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Quick, or we\rquote ll lose him,\rdblquote  said Harry, speeding up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Our feet\rquote ll be seen!\rdblquote  said Hermione anxiously, as the cloak flapped a little around their ankles; it was much more difficult hid\-ing all three of them under the cloak nowadays.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It doesn\rquote t matter,\rdblquote  said Harry impatiently. \ldblquote Just hurry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Knockturn Alley, the side street devoted to the Dark Arts, looked completely deserted. They peered into windows as they passed, but none of the shops seemed to have any customers at all. Harry supposed it was a bit of a giveaway in these dangerous and suspicious times to buy Dark artifacts \emdash  or at least, to be seen buy\-ing them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione gave his arm a hard pinch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ouch!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Shh! Look! He\rquote s in there!\rdblquote  she breathed in Harry\rquote s ear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had drawn level with the only shop in Knockturn Alley that Harry had ever visited, Borgin and Burkes, which sold a wide variety of sinister objects. There in the midst of the cases full of skulls and old bottles stood Draco Malfoy with his back to them, just visible beyond the very same large black cabinet in which Harry had once hidden to avoid Malfoy and his father. Judging by the movements of Malfoy\rquote s hands, he was talking animatedly. The proprietor of the shop, Mr. Borgin, an oily-haired, stooping man, stood facing Malfoy. He was wearing a curious expression of min\-gled resentment and fear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If only we could hear what they\rquote re saying!\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We can!\rdblquote  said Ron excitedly. \ldblquote Hang on \emdash  damn \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He dropped a couple more of the boxes he was still clutching as he fumbled with the largest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Extendable Ears, look!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fantastic!\rdblquote  said Hermione, as Ron unraveled the long, flesh\-colored strings and began to feed them toward the bottom of the door. \ldblquote Oh, I hope the door isn\rquote t Imperturbable \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Ron gleefully. \ldblquote Listen!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They put their heads together and listened intently to the ends of the strings, through which Malfoy\rquote s voice could be heard loud and clear, as though a radio had been turned on.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 you know how to fix it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Possibly,\rdblquote  said Borgin, in a tone that suggested he was unwill\-ing to commit himself. \ldblquote I\rquote ll need to see it, though. Why don\rquote t you bring it into the shop?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I can\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote It\rquote s got to stay put. I just need you to tell me how to do it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry saw Borgin lick his lips nervously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, without seeing it, I must say it will be a very difficult job, perhaps impossible. I couldn\rquote t guarantee anything.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No?\rdblquote  said Malfoy, and Harry knew, just by his tone, that Mal\-foy was sneering. \ldblquote Perhaps this will make you more confident.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He moved toward Borgin and was blocked from view by the cabinet. Harry, Ron, and Hermione shuffled sideways to try and keep him in sight, but all they could see was Borgin, looking very frightened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Tell anyone,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, \ldblquote and there will be retribution. You know Fenrir Greyback? He\rquote s a family friend. He\rquote ll be dropping in from time to time to make sure you\rquote re giving the problem your full attention.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There will be no need for \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll decide that,\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote Well, I\rquote d better be off. And don\rquote t forget to keep \i that\i0  one safe, I\rquote ll need it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Perhaps you\rquote d like to take it now?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, of course I wouldn\rquote t, you stupid little man, how would I look carrying that down the street? Just don\rquote t sell it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course not\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 sir.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Borgin made a bow as deep as the one Harry had once seen him give Lucius Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not a word to anyone, Borgin, and that includes my mother, understand?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Naturally, naturally,\rdblquote  murmured Borgin, bowing again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Next moment, the bell over the door tinkled loudly as Malfoy stalked out of the shop looking very pleased with himself. He passed so close to Harry, Ron, and Hermione that they felt the cloak flutter around their knees again. Inside the shop, Borgin remained frozen; his unctuous smile had vanished; he looked worried.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What was that about?\rdblquote  whispered Ron, reeling in the Extend\-able Ears.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry, thinking hard. \ldblquote He wants something mended \'85 and he wants to reserve something in there. \'85 Could you see what he pointed at when he said \lquote that one\rquote ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, he was behind that cabinet \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You two stay here,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are you \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Hermione had already ducked out from under the cloak. She checked her hair in the reflection in the glass, then marched into the shop, setting the bell tinkling again. Ron hastily fed the Extendable Ears back under the door and passed one of the strings to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hello, horrible morning, isn\rquote t it?\rdblquote  Hermione said brightly to Borgin, who did not answer, but cast her a suspicious look. Hum\-ming cheerily, Hermione strolled through the jumble of objects on display.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is this necklace for sale?\rdblquote  she asked, pausing beside a glass-fronted case.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you\rquote ve got one and a half thousand Galleons,\rdblquote  said Mr. Borgin coldly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \emdash  er \emdash  no, I haven\rquote t got quite that much,\rdblquote  said Hermi\-one, walking on. \ldblquote And \'85 what about this lovely \emdash  um \emdash  skull?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sixteen Galleons.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So it\rquote s for sale, then? It isn\rquote t being \'85 kept for anyone?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mr. Borgin squinted at her. Harry had the nasty feeling he knew exactly what Hermione was up to. Apparently Hermione felt she had been rumbled too because she suddenly threw caution to the winds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The thing is, that \emdash  er \emdash  boy who was in here just now, Draco Malfoy, well, he\rquote s a friend of mine, and I want to get him a birthday present, but if he\rquote s already reserved anything, I obviously don\rquote t want to get him the same thing, so \'85 um \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was a pretty lame story in Harry\rquote s opinion, and apparently Borgin thought so too.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Out,\rdblquote  he said sharply. \ldblquote Get out!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione did not wait to be asked twice, but hurried to the door with Borgin at her heels. As the bell tinkled again, Borgin slammed the door behind her and put up the closed sign.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ah well,\rdblquote  said Ron, throwing the cloak back over Hermione. \ldblquote Worth a try, but you were a bit obvious \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, next time you can show me how it\rquote s done, Master of Mystery!\rdblquote  she snapped.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Hermione bickered all the way back to Weasleys\rquote\lang3081  \lang1033 Wizard Wheezes, where they were forced to stop so that they could dodge undetected around a very anxious-looking Mrs. Weasley and Hagrid, who had clearly noticed their absence. Once in the shop, Harry whipped off the Invisibility Cloak, hid it in his bag, and joined in with the other two when they insisted, in answer to Mrs. Weasley\rquote s accusations, that they had been in the back room all along, and that she could not have looked properly.\lang3081\par
