\lang1033\ldblquote I enjoyed the meetings too,\rdblquote  said Luna serenely. \ldblquote It was like having friends.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 This was one of those uncomfortable things Luna often said and which made Harry feel a squirming mixture of pity and embarrass\-ment. Before he could respond, however, there was a disturbance outside their compartment door; a group of fourth-year girls was whispering and giggling together on the other side of the glass.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You ask him!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll do it!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And one of them, a bold-looking girl with large dark eyes, a prominent chin, and long black hair pushed her way through the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, Harry, I\rquote m Romilda, Romilda Vane,\rdblquote  she said loudly and confidently. \ldblquote Why don\rquote t you join us in our compartment? You don\rquote t have to sit with \i them,\i0\rdblquote  she added in a stage whisper, indicat\-ing Neville\rquote s bottom, which was sticking out from under the seat again as he groped around for Trevor, and Luna, who was now wearing her free Spectrespecs, which gave her the look of a de\-mented, multicolored owl.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They\rquote re friends of mine,\rdblquote  said Harry coldly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh,\rdblquote  said the girl, looking very surprised. \ldblquote Oh. Okay.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And she withdrew, sliding the door closed behind her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote People expect you to have cooler friends than us,\rdblquote  said Luna, once again displaying her knack for embarrassing honesty.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are cool,\rdblquote  said Harry shortly. \ldblquote None of them was at the Ministry. They didn\rquote t fight with me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s a very nice thing to say,\rdblquote  beamed Luna. Then she pushed her Spectrespecs farther up her nose and settled down to read \i The Quibbler.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We didn\rquote t face \i him,\i0  though,\rdblquote  said Neville, emerging from un\-der the seat with fluff and dust in his hair and a resigned-looking Trevor in his hand. \ldblquote You did. You should hear my gran talk about you. \lquote\i That Harry Potter\rquote s got more backbone than the whole Ministry of Magic put together\i0 !\rquote\i  \i0 She\rquote d give anything to have you as a grand\-son. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry laughed uncomfortably and changed the subject to O.W.L. results as soon as he could. While Neville recited his grades and wondered aloud whether he would be allowed to take a Trans\-figuration N.E.W.T. with only an \ldblquote Acceptable,\rdblquote  Harry watched him without really listening.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville\rquote s childhood had been blighted by Voldemort just as much as Harry\rquote s had, but Neville had no idea how close he had come to having Harry\rquote s destiny. The prophecy could have referred to either of them, yet, for his own inscrutable reasons, Voldemort had chosen to believe that Harry was the one meant.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Had Voldemort chosen Neville, it would be Neville sitting op\-posite Harry bearing the lightning-shaped scar and the weight of the prophecy. \'85 Or would it? Would Neville\rquote s mother have died to save him, as Lily had died for Harry? Surely she would. \'85 But what if she had been unable to stand between her son and Volde\-mort? Would there then have been no \ldblquote Chosen One\rdblquote  at all? An\lang3081  \lang1033 empty seat where Neville now sat and a scarless Harry who would have been kissed good-bye by his own mother, not Ron\rquote s?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You all right, Harry? You look funny,\rdblquote  said Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry started. \ldblquote Sorry \emdash  I \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wrackspurt got you?\rdblquote  asked Luna sympathetically, peering at Harry through her enormous colored spectacles.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \emdash\lang3081  \lang1033 what?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A Wrackspurt\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 They\rquote re invisible. They float in through your ears and make your brain go fuzzy,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote I thought I felt one zooming around in here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She flapped her hands at thin air, as though beating off large invisible moths. Harry and Neville caught each other\rquote s eyes and hastily began to talk of Quidditch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The weather beyond the train windows was as patchy as it had been all summer; they passed through stretches of the chilling mist, then out into weak, clear sunlight. It was during one of the clear spells, when the sun was visible almost directly overhead, that Ron and Hermione entered the compartment at last.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wish the lunch trolley would hurry up, I\rquote m starving,\rdblquote  said Ron longingly, slumping into the seat beside Harry and rubbing his stomach. \ldblquote Hi, Neville. Hi, Luna. Guess what?\rdblquote  he added, turning to Harry. \ldblquote Malfoy\rquote s not doing prefect duty. He\rquote s just sitting in his compartment with the other Slytherins, we saw him when we passed.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry sat up straight, interested. It was not like Malfoy to pass up the chance to demonstrate his power as prefect, which he had happily abused all the previous year.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What did he do when he saw you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The usual,\rdblquote  said Ron indifferently, demonstrating a rude hand\lang3081  \lang1033 gesture. \ldblquote Not like him, though, is it? Well \emdash  \i that\i0  is\rdblquote  \emdash  he did the hand gesture again \emdash  \ldblquote but why isn\rquote t he out there bullying first years?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry, but his mind was racing. Didn\rquote t this look as though Malfoy had more important things on his mind than bullying younger students?\lang3081\par
