\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t think so,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote I think he\rquote s \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But before he could expound on his theory, the compartment door slid open again and a breathless third-year girl stepped inside.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m supposed to deliver these to Neville Longbottom and Harry P-Potter,\rdblquote  she faltered, as her eyes met Harry\rquote s and she turned scar\-let. She was holding out two scrolls of parchment tied with violet ribbon. Perplexed, Harry and Neville took the scroll addressed to each of them and the girl stumbled back out of the compartment.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is it?\rdblquote  Ron demanded, as Harry unrolled his.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote An invitation,\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\par
\i Harry,\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\i I would be delighted if you would join me for a bite of lunch in compartment C.\lang3081\i0\par
