\lang1033\ldblquote I just tried a few of the tips written in the margins, honestly, Ginny, there\rquote s nothing funny \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ginny\rquote s got a point,\rdblquote  said Hermione, perking up at once. \ldblquote We\lang3081  \lang1033 ought to check that there\rquote s nothing odd about it. I mean, all these funny instructions, who knows?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hey!\rdblquote  said Harry indignantly, as she pulled his copy of \i Advanced Potion-Making\i0  out of his bag and raised her wand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Specialis Revelio\i0 !\rdblquote  she said, rapping it smartly on the front cover.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nothing whatsoever happened. The book simply lay there, look\-ing old and dirty and dog-eared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Finished?\rdblquote  said Harry irritably. \ldblquote Or d\rquote you want to wait and see if it does a few backflips?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It seems all right,\rdblquote  said Hermione, still staring at the book sus\-piciously. \ldblquote I mean, it really does seem to be \'85 just a textbook.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good. Then I\rquote ll have it back,\rdblquote  said Harry, snatching it off the table, but it slipped from his hand and landed open on the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nobody else was looking. Harry bent low to retrieve the book, and as he did so, he saw something scribbled along the bottom of the back cover in the same small, cramped handwriting as the in\-structions that had won him his bottle of Felix Felicis, now safely hidden inside a pair of socks in his trunk upstairs. \par
\par
