\lang1033\ldblquote That old man was \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Voldemort\rquote s grandfather, yes,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote Marvolo, his son, Morfin, and his daughter, Merope, were the last of the Gaunts, a very ancient Wizarding family noted for a vein of insta\-bility and violence that flourished through the generations due to their habit of marrying their own cousins. Lack of sense coupled with a great liking for grandeur meant that the family gold was squandered several generations before Marvolo was born. He, as you saw, was left in squalor and poverty, with a very nasty temper, a fantastic amount of arrogance and pride, and a couple of family heirlooms that he treasured just as much as his son, and rather more than his daughter.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So Merope,\rdblquote  said Harry, leaning forward in his chair and star\-ing at Dumbledore, \ldblquote so Merope was \'85 Sir, does that mean she was \'85 \i Voldemort\rquote s mother\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It does,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote And it so happens that we also had a glimpse of Voldemort\rquote s father. I wonder whether you noticed?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
