As Hermione had predicted, the sixth years\rquote  free periods were not the hours of blissful relaxation Ron had antici\-pated, but times in which to attempt to keep up with the vast amount of homework they were being set. Not only were they studying as though they had exams every day, but the lessons them\-selves had become more demanding than ever before. Harry barely understood half of what Professor McGonagall said to them these days; even Hermione had had to ask her to repeat instructions once or twice. Incredibly, and to Hermione\rquote s increasing resentment, Harry\rquote s best subject had suddenly become Potions, thanks to the Half-Blood Prince.\par
Nonverbal spells were now expected, not only in Defense Against the Dark Arts, but in Charms and Transfiguration too. Harry frequently looked over at his classmates in the common room or at mealtimes to see them purple in the face and straining as though they had overdosed on U-No-Poo; but he knew that they\lang3081  \lang1033 were really struggling to make spells work without saying incanta\-tions aloud. It was a relief to get outside into the greenhouses; they were dealing with more dangerous plants than ever in Herbology, but at least they were still allowed to swear loudly if the Venomous Tentacula seized them unexpectedly from behind.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 One result of their enormous workload and the frantic hours of practicing nonverbal spells was that Harry, Ron, and Hermione had so far been unable to find time to go and visit Hagrid. He had stopped coming to meals at the staff table, an ominous sign, and on the few occasions when they had passed him in the corridors or out in the grounds, he had mysteriously failed to notice them or hear their greetings.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ve got to go and explain,\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking up at Hagrid\rquote s huge empty chair at the staff table the following Saturday at breakfast.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ve got Quidditch tryouts this morning!\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote\i And \i0 we\rquote re supposed to be practicing that Aguamenti Charm from Flitwick! Anyway, explain what? How are we going to tell him we hated his stupid subject?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We didn\rquote t hate it!\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
