\lang1033\ldblquote I hate not talking to Hagrid,\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking upset.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ll go down after Quidditch,\rdblquote  Harry assured her. He too was missing Hagrid, although like Ron he thought that they were bet\-ter off without Grawp in their lives. \ldblquote But trials might take all morning, the number of people who have applied.\rdblquote  He felt slightly\lang3081  \lang1033 nervous at confronting the first hurdle of his Captaincy. \ldblquote I dunno why the team\rquote s this popular all of a sudden.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, come on, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione, suddenly impatient. \ldblquote It\rquote s not \i Quidditch\i0  that\rquote s popular, it\rquote s you! You\rquote ve never been more in\-teresting, and frankly, you\rquote ve never been more fanciable.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron gagged on a large piece of kipper. Hermione spared him one look of disdain before turning back to Harry.\lang3081\par
