\lang1033\ldblquote I think it\rquote s fascinating,\rdblquote  said Hermione earnestly. \ldblquote It makes\lang3081  \lang1033 absolute sense to know as much about Voldemort as possible. How else will you find out his weaknesses?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So how was Slughorn\rquote s latest party?\rdblquote  Harry asked her thickly through the gum shield.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, it was quite fun, really,\rdblquote  said Hermione, now putting on protective goggles. \ldblquote I mean, he drones on about famous ex-pupils a bit, and he absolutely \i fawns\i0  on McLaggen because he\rquote s so well-connected, but he gave us some really nice food and he introduced us to Gwenog Jones.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Gwenog Jones?\rdblquote  said Ron, his eyes widening under his own goggles. \ldblquote\i The\i0  Gwenog Jones? Captain of the Holyhead Harpies?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Personally, I thought she was a bit full of herself, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Quite\i0  enough chat over here!\rdblquote  said Professor Sprout briskly, bustling over and looking stern. \ldblquote You\rquote re lagging behind, everybody else has started, and Neville\rquote s already got his first pod!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They looked around; sure enough, there sat Neville with a bloody lip and several nasty scratches along the side of his face, but clutching an unpleasantly pulsating green object about the size of a grapefruit.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, Professor, we\rquote re starting now!\rdblquote  said Ron, adding quietly, when she had turned away again, \ldblquote should\rquote ve used Muffliato, Harry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, we shouldn\rquote t!\rdblquote  said Hermione at once, looking, as she al\-ways did, intensely cross at the thought of the Half-Blood Prince and his spells. \ldblquote Well, come on \'85 we\rquote d better get going. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She gave the other two an apprehensive look; they all took deep breaths and then dived at the gnarled stump between them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It sprang to life at once; long, prickly, bramblelike vines flew out of the top and whipped through the air. One tangled itself in\lang3081  \lang1033 Hermione\rquote s hair, and Ron beat it back with a pair of secateurs; Harry succeeded in trapping a couple of vines and knotting them together; a hole opened in the middle of all the tentaclelike branches; Hermione plunged her arm bravely into this hole, which closed like a trap around her elbow; Harry and Ron tugged and wrenched at the vines, forcing the hole to open again, and Hermi\-one snatched her arm free, clutching in her fingers a pod just like Neville\rquote s. At once, the prickly vines shot back inside, and the gnarled stump sat there looking like an innocently dead lump of wood.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You know, I don\rquote t think I\rquote ll be having any of these in my garden when I\rquote ve got my own place,\rdblquote  said Ron, pushing his goggles up onto his forehead and wiping sweat from his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Pass me a bowl,\rdblquote  said Hermione, holding the pulsating pod at arm\rquote s length; Harry handed one over and she dropped the pod into it with a look of disgust on her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be squeamish, squeeze it out, they\rquote re best when they\rquote re fresh!\rdblquote  called Professor Sprout.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Anyway,\rdblquote  said Hermione, continuing their interrupted conver\-sation as though a lump of wood had not just attacked them, \ldblquote Slughorn\rquote s going to have a Christmas party, Harry, and there\rquote s no way you\rquote ll be able to wriggle out of this one because he actually asked me to check your free evenings, so he could be sure to have it on a night you can come.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry groaned. Meanwhile, Ron, who was attempting to burst the pod in the bowl by putting both hands on it, standing up, and squashing it as hard as he could, said angrily, \ldblquote And this is another party just for Slughorn\rquote s favorites, is it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just for the Slug Club, yes,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The pod flew out from under Ron\rquote s fingers and hit the green\-house glass, rebounding onto the back of Professor Sprout\rquote s head and knocking off her old, patched hat. Harry went to retrieve the pod; when he got back, Hermione was saying, \ldblquote Look, \i I\lang3081\i0  \lang1033 didn\rquote t make up the name \lquote Slug Club\rquote  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i Slug Club,\i0\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\i  \lang1033\i0 repeated Ron with a sneer worthy of Malfoy. \ldblquote It\rquote s pathetic. Well, I hope you enjoy your party. Why don\rquote t you try hooking up with McLaggen, then Slughorn can make you King and Queen Slug \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re allowed to bring guests,\rdblquote  said Hermione, who for some reason had turned a bright, boiling scarlet, \ldblquote and I was \i going\i0  to ask you to come, but if you think it\rquote s that stupid then I won\rquote t bother!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry suddenly wished the pod had flown a little farther, so that he need not have been sitting here with the pair of them. Unno\-ticed by either, he seized the bowl that contained the pod and be\-gan to try and open it by the noisiest and most energetic means he could think of; unfortunately, he could still hear every word of their conversation.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You were going to ask me?\rdblquote  asked Ron, in a completely differ\-ent voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Hermione angrily. \ldblquote But obviously if you\rquote d rather I \i hooked up with McLaggen \i0\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a pause while Harry continued to pound the resilient pod with a trowel.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I wouldn\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Ron, in a very quiet voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry missed the pod, hit the bowl, and shattered it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Reparo,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 he said hastily, poking the pieces with his wand, and the bowl sprang back together again. The crash, however, appeared to have awoken Ron and Hermione to Harry\rquote s presence. Hermione\lang3081  \lang1033 looked flustered and immediately started fussing about for her copy of\lang3081  \lang1033\i Flesh-Eating Trees of the World\i0  to find out the correct way to juice Snargaluff pods; Ron, on the other hand, looked sheepish but also rather pleased with himself.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hand that over, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione hurriedly. \ldblquote It says we\rquote re supposed to puncture them with something sharp. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
