Snow was swirling against the icy windows once more;\lang3081  \lang1033 Christ\-mas was approaching fast. Hagrid had already single-handedly delivered the usual twelve Christmas trees for the Great Hall; gar\-lands of holly and tinsel had been twisted around the banisters of the stairs; everlasting candles glowed from inside the helmets of suits of armor and great bunches of mistletoe had been hung at in\-tervals along the corridors. Large groups of girls tended to converge underneath the mistletoe bunches every time Harry went past, which caused blockages in the corridors; fortunately, however, Harry\rquote s frequent nighttime wanderings had given him an unusually good knowledge of the castle\rquote s secret passageways, so that he was able, without too much difficulty, to navigate mistletoe-free routes between classes.\par
Ron, who might once have found the necessity of these detours a cause for jealousy rather than hilarity, simply roared with laugh\-ter about it all. Although Harry much preferred this new laughing,\lang3081  \lang1033 joking Ron to the moody, aggressive model he had been enduring for the last few weeks, the improved Ron came at a heavy price. Firstly, Harry had to put up with the frequent presence of Laven\-der Brown, who seemed to regard any moment that she was not kissing Ron as a moment wasted; and secondly, Harry found him\-self once more the best friend of two people who seemed unlikely ever to speak to each other again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron, whose hands and forearms still bore scratches and cuts from Hermione\rquote s bird attack, was taking a defensive and resentful tone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She can\rquote t complain,\rdblquote  he told Harry. \ldblquote She snogged Krum. So she\rquote s found out someone wants to snog me too. Well, it\rquote s a free country. I haven\rquote t done anything wrong.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not answer, but pretended to be absorbed in the book they were supposed to have read before Charms next morning (\i Quintessence\i0 : \i A Quest\i0 ). Determined as he was to remain friends with both Ron and Hermione, he was spending a lot of time with his mouth shut tight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I never promised Hermione anything,\rdblquote  Ron mumbled. \ldblquote I mean, all right, I was going to go to Slughorn\rquote s Christmas party with her, but she never said \'85 just as friends \'85 I\rquote m a free agent. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry turned a page of \i Quintessence,\i0  aware that Ron was watch\-ing him. Ron\rquote s voice tailed away in mutters, barely audible over the loud crackling of the fire, though Harry thought he caught the words \ldblquote Krum\rdblquote  and \ldblquote can\rquote t complain\rdblquote  again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione\rquote s schedule was so full that Harry could only talk to her properly in the evenings, when Ron was, in any case, so tightly\lang3081  \lang1033 wrapped around Lavender that he did not notice what Harry was doing. Hermione refused to sit in the common room while Ron was there, so Harry generally joined her in the library, which meant that their conversations were held in whispers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s at perfect liberty to kiss whomever he likes,\rdblquote  said Hermi\-one, while the librarian, Madam Pince, prowled the shelves behind them. \ldblquote I really couldn\rquote t care less.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She raised her quill and dotted an \i i \i0 so ferociously that she punc\-tured a hole in her parchment. Harry said nothing. He thought his voice might soon vanish from lack of use. He bent a little lower over \i Advanced Potion-Making\i0  and continued to make notes on Everlasting Elixirs, occasionally pausing to decipher the Prince\rquote s useful additions to Libatius Borage\rquote s text.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And incidentally,\rdblquote  said Hermione, after a few moments, \ldblquote you need to be careful.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote For the last time,\rdblquote  said Harry, speaking in a slightly hoarse whisper after three-quarters of an hour of silence, \ldblquote I am not giving back this book, I\rquote ve learned more from the Half-Blood Prince than Snape or Slughorn have taught me in \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not talking about your stupid so-called Prince,\rdblquote  said Her\-mione, giving his book a nasty look as though it had been rude to her. \ldblquote I\rquote m talking about earlier. I went into the girls\rquote  bathroom just before I came in here and there were about a dozen girls in there, including that Romilda Vane, trying to decide how to slip you a love potion. They\rquote re all hoping they\rquote re going to get you to take them to Slughorn\rquote s party, and they all seem to have bought Fred and George\rquote s love potions, which I\rquote m afraid to say probably work \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why didn\rquote t you confiscate them then?\rdblquote  demanded Harry. It seemed extraordinary that Hermione\rquote s mania for upholding rules could have abandoned her at this crucial juncture.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They didn\rquote t have the potions with them in the bathroom,\rdblquote  said Hermione scornfully. \ldblquote They were just discussing tactics. As I doubt whether even the \i Half-Blood Prince\i0\rdblquote  \emdash  she gave the book another nasty look\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  \ldblquote could dream up an antidote for a dozen different love potions at once, I\rquote d just invite someone to go with you, that\rquote ll stop all the others thinking they\rquote ve still got a chance. It\rquote s tomorrow night, they\rquote re getting desperate.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There isn\rquote t anyone I want to invite,\rdblquote  mumbled Harry, who was still trying not to think about Ginny any more than he could help, despite the fact that she kept cropping up in his dreams in ways that made him devoutly thankful that Ron could not perform Legilimency.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, just be careful what you drink, because Romilda Vane looked like she meant business,\rdblquote  said Hermione grimly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She hitched up the long roll of parchment on which she was writing her Arithmancy essay and continued to scratch away with her quill. Harry watched her with his mind a long way away.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hang on a moment,\rdblquote  he said slowly. \ldblquote I thought Filch had banned anything bought at Weasleys\rquote  Wizard Wheezes?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And when has anyone ever paid attention to what Filch has banned?\rdblquote  asked Hermione, still concentrating on her essay.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But I thought all the owls were being searched. So how come these girls are able to bring love potions into school?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
