\lang1033\ldblquote Well, good night, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione, though it was only seven o\rquote clock in the evening, and she left for the girls\rquote  dormitory without another word.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry went to bed comforting himself that there was only one more day of lessons to struggle through, plus Slughorn\rquote s party, after which he and Ron would depart together for the Burrow. It now seemed impossible that Ron and Hermione would make up with each other before the holidays began, but perhaps, somehow, the break would give them time to calm down, think better of their behavior. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But his hopes were not high, and they sank still lower after en\-during a Transfiguration lesson with them both next day. They had just embarked upon the immensely difficult topic of human Trans\-figuration; working in front of mirrors, they were supposed to be changing the color of their own eyebrows. Hermione laughed\lang3081  \lang1033 unkindly at Ron\rquote s disastrous first attempt, during which he some\-how managed to give himself a spectacular handlebar mustache; Ron retaliated by doing a cruel but accurate impression of Hermi\-one jumping up and down in her seat every time Professor McGon\-agall asked a question, which Lavender and Parvati found deeply amusing and which reduced Hermione to the verge of tears again. She raced out of the classroom on the bell, leaving half her things behind; Harry, deciding that her need was greater than Ron\rquote s just now, scooped up her remaining possessions and followed her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He finally tracked her down as she emerged from a girls\rquote  bath\-room on the floor below. She was accompanied by Luna Lovegood, who was patting her vaguely on the back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, hello, Harry,\rdblquote  said Luna. \ldblquote Did you know one of your eye\-brows is bright yellow?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, Luna. Hermione, you left your stuff. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He held out her books.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a choked voice, taking her things and turning away quickly to hide the fact that she was wiping her eyes on her pencil case. \ldblquote Thank you, Harry. Well, I\rquote d better get go\-ing. \'85\lang3081\rdblquote\par
\lang1033 And she hurried off, without giving Harry any time to offer words of comfort, though admittedly he could not think of any.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She\rquote s a bit upset,\rdblquote  said Luna. \ldblquote I thought at first it was Moaning Myrtle in there, but it turned out to be Hermione. She said some\-thing about that Ron Weasley. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, they\rquote ve had a row,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He says very funny things sometimes, doesn\rquote t he?\rdblquote  said Luna, as they set off down the corridor together. \ldblquote But he can be a bit un\-kind. I noticed that last year.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I s\rquote pose,\rdblquote  said Harry. Luna was demonstrating her usual knack of speaking uncomfortable truths; he had never met anyone quite like her. \ldblquote So have you had a good term?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, it\rquote s been all right,\rdblquote  said Luna. \ldblquote A bit lonely without the D.A. Ginny\rquote s been nice, though. She stopped two boys in our Transfiguration class calling me \lquote Loony\rquote  the other day \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How would you like to come to Slughorn\rquote s party with me tonight?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The words were out of Harry\rquote s mouth before he could stop them; he heard himself say them as though it were a stranger speaking.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Luna turned her protuberant eyes upon him in surprise.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Slughorn\rquote s party? With you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote We\rquote re supposed to bring guests, so I thought you might like \'85 I mean \'85\rdblquote  He was keen to make his intentions perfectly clear. \ldblquote I mean, just as friends, you know. But if you don\rquote t want to \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
