\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry firmly, \ldblquote that was a mistake. I\rquote ll get Hermione to put it right for me. So, I\rquote ll meet you in the entrance hall at eight o\rquote clock then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote AHA!\rdblquote  screamed a voice from overhead and both of them jumped; unnoticed by either of them, they had just passed right underneath Peeves, who was hanging upside down from a chande\-lier and grinning maliciously at them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Potty asked Loony to go to the party\i0 !\i  Potty lurves Loony\i0 !\i  Potty luuuuurves Looooooony\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he zoomed away, cackling and shrieking, \ldblquote Potty loves Loony!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nice to keep these things private,\rdblquote  said Harry. And sure enough, in no time at all the whole school seemed to know that Harry Potter was taking Luna Lovegood to Slughorn\rquote s party.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You could\rquote ve taken \i anyone\i0 !\rdblquote  said Ron in disbelief over dinner. \ldblquote\i Anyone\i0 ! And you chose Loony Lovegood?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t call her that, Ron,\rdblquote  snapped Ginny, pausing behind Harry on her way to join friends. \ldblquote I\rquote m really glad you\rquote re taking her, Harry, she\rquote s so excited.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And she moved on down the table to sit with Dean. Harry tried to feel pleased that Ginny was glad he was taking Luna to the party, but could not quite manage it. A long way along the table, Hermi\-one was sitting alone, playing with her stew. Harry noticed Ron looking at her furtively.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You could say sorry,\rdblquote  suggested Harry bluntly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What, and get attacked by another flock of canaries?\rdblquote  muttered Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What did you have to imitate her for?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She laughed at my mustache!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So did I, it was the stupidest thing I\rquote ve ever seen.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Ron did not seem to have heard; Lavender had just arrived with Parvati. Squeezing herself in between Harry and Ron, Laven\-der flung her arms around Ron\rquote s neck.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, Harry,\rdblquote  said Parvati who, like him, looked faintly embar\-rassed and bored by the behavior of their two friends.\lang3081\par
