\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Hermione sweetly. \ldblquote The one who \i almost\i0\rdblquote  \emdash  she put a great deal of emphasis on the word \emdash  \ldblquote became Gryffin\-dor Keeper.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you going out with him, then?\rdblquote  asked Parvati, wide-eyed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \emdash  yes \emdash  didn\rquote t you know?\rdblquote  said Hermione, with a most un-Hermione-ish giggle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Parvati, looking positively agog at this piece of gossip. \ldblquote Wow, you like your Quidditch players, don\rquote t you? First Krum, then McLaggen \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I like \i really good\i0  Quidditch players,\rdblquote  Hermione corrected her, still smiling. \ldblquote Well, see you \'85 Got to go and get ready for the party. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She left. At once Lavender and Parvati put their heads together to discuss this new development, with everything they had ever heard about McLaggen, and all they had ever guessed about Her\-mione. Ron looked strangely blank and said nothing. Harry was left to ponder in silence the depths to which girls would sink to get revenge.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 When he arrived in the entrance hall at eight o\rquote clock that night, he found an unusually large number of girls lurking there, all of whom seemed to be staring at him resentfully as he approached Luna. She was wearing a set of spangled silver robes that were at\-tracting a certain amount of giggles from the onlookers, but other\-wise she looked quite nice. Harry was glad, in any case, that she had left off her radish earrings, her butterbeer cork necklace, and her Spectrespecs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote Shall we get going then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes,\rdblquote  she said happily. \ldblquote Where is the party?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Slughorn\rquote s office,\rdblquote  said Harry, leading her up the marble stair\-case away from all the staring and muttering. \ldblquote Did you hear, there\rquote s supposed to be a vampire coming?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
