\lang1033 Harry, who thought it most unlikely that Rufus Scrimgeour was a vampire, but who was used to Luna repeating her father\rquote s bizarre\lang3081  \lang1033 views as though they were fact, did not reply; they were already approaching Slughorn\rquote s office and the sounds of laughter, music, and loud conversation were growing louder with every step they took.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Whether it had been built that way, or because he had used mag\-ical trickery to make it so, Slughorn\rquote s office was much larger than the usual teacher\rquote s study. The ceiling and walls had been draped with emerald, crimson, and gold hangings, so that it looked as though they were all inside a vast tent. The room was crowded and stuffy and bathed in the red light cast by an ornate golden lamp dangling from the center of the ceiling in which real fairies were fluttering, each a brilliant speck of light. Loud singing accompa\-nied by what sounded like mandolins issued from a distant corner; a haze of pipe smoke hung over several elderly warlocks deep in conversation, and a number of house-elves were negotiating their way squeakily through the forest of knees, obscured by the heavy silver platters of food they were bearing, so that they looked like lit\-tle roving tables.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, m\rquote boy!\rdblquote  boomed Slughorn, almost as soon as Harry and Luna had squeezed in through the door. \ldblquote Come in, come in, so many people I\rquote d like you to meet!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn was wearing a tasseled velvet hat to match his smoking jacket. Gripping Harry\rquote s arm so tightly he might have been hoping to Disapparate with him, Slughorn led him purposefully into the party; Harry seized Luna\rquote s hand and dragged her along with him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, I\rquote d like you to meet Eldred Worple, an old student of mine, author of \i Blood Brothers: My Life Amongst the Vampires\i0  \emdash  and, of course, his friend Sanguini.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Worple, who was a small, stout, bespectacled man, grabbed\lang3081  \lang1033 Harry\rquote s hand and shook it enthusiastically; the vampire Sanguini, who was tall and emaciated with dark shadows under his eyes, merely nodded. He looked rather bored. A gaggle of girls was standing close to him, looking curious and excited.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter, I am simply delighted!\rdblquote  said Worple, peering shortsightedly up into Harry\rquote s face. \ldblquote I was saying to Professor Slughorn only the other day, \lquote\i Where is the biography of Harry Potter for which we have all been waiting\i0 ?\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Er,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote were you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just as modest as Horace described!\rdblquote  said Worple. \ldblquote But seri\-ously\rdblquote  \emdash  his manner changed; it became suddenly businesslike \emdash  \ldblquote I would be delighted to write it myself\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  people are craving to know more about you, dear boy, craving! If you were prepared to grant me a few interviews, say in four- or five-hour sessions, why, we could have the book finished within months. And all with very little effort on your part, I assure you \emdash  ask Sanguini here if it isn\rquote t quite \emdash  \i Sanguini, stay here\i0 !\rdblquote  added Worple, suddenly stern, for the vampire had been edging toward the nearby group of girls, a rather hungry look in his eye. \ldblquote Here, have a pasty,\rdblquote  said Worple, seizing one from a passing elf and stuffing it into Sanguini\rquote s hand before turning his attention back to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My dear boy, the gold you could make, you have no idea \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m definitely not interested,\rdblquote  said Harry firmly, \ldblquote and I\rquote ve just seen a friend of mine, sorry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pulled Luna after him into the crowd; he had indeed just seen a long mane of brown hair disappear between what looked like two members of the Weird Sisters.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione! \i Hermione\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry! There you are, thank goodness! Hi, Luna!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s happened to you?\rdblquote  asked Harry, for Hermione looked distinctly disheveled, rather as though she had just fought her way out of a thicket of Devil\rquote s Snare.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, I\rquote ve just escaped \emdash  I mean, I\rquote ve just left Cormac,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote Under the mistletoe,\rdblquote  she added in explanation, as Harry continued to look questioningly at her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Serves you right for coming with him,\rdblquote  he told her severely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought he\rquote d annoy Ron most,\rdblquote  said Hermione dispassion\-ately. \ldblquote I debated for a while about Zacharias Smith, but I thought, on the whole \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i You considered Smith\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Harry, revolted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, I did, and I\rquote m starting to wish I\rquote d chosen him, McLaggen makes Grawp look a gentleman. Let\rquote s go this way, we\rquote ll be able to see him coming, he\rquote s so tall. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The three of them made their way over to the other side of the room, scooping up goblets of mead on the way, realizing too late that Professor Trelawney was standing there alone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hello,\rdblquote  said Luna politely to Professor Trelawney.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good evening, my dear,\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney, focusing upon Luna with some difficulty. Harry could smell cooking sherry again. \ldblquote I haven\rquote t seen you in my classes lately. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I\rquote ve got Firenze this year,\rdblquote  said Luna.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, of course,\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney with an angry, drunken titter. \ldblquote Or Dobbin, as I prefer to think of him. You would have thought, would you not, that now I am returned to the school Professor Dumbledore might have got rid of the horse? But no \'85 we share classes. \'85 It\rquote s an insult, frankly, an insult. Do you know\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Trelawney seemed too tipsy to have recognized Harry.\lang3081  \lang1033 Under cover of her furious criticisms of Firenze, Harry drew closer to Hermione and said, \ldblquote Let\rquote s get something straight. Are you plan\-ning to tell Ron that you interfered at Keeper tryouts?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione raised her eyebrows. \ldblquote Do you really think I\rquote d stoop that low?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked at her shrewdly. \ldblquote Hermione, if you can ask out McLaggen \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s a difference,\rdblquote  said Hermione with dignity. \ldblquote I\rquote ve got no plans to tell Ron anything about what might, or might not, have happened at Keeper tryouts.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good,\rdblquote  said Harry fervently. \ldblquote Because he\rquote ll just fall apart again, and we\rquote ll lose the next match \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Quidditch!\rdblquote  said Hermione angrily. \ldblquote Is that all boys care about? Cormac hasn\rquote t asked me one single question about myself, no, I\rquote ve just been treated to \lquote A Hundred Great Saves Made by Cormac McLaggen\rquote  nonstop ever since \emdash  oh no, here he comes!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She moved so fast it was as though she had Disapparated; one moment she was there, the next, she had squeezed between two guffawing witches and vanished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Seen Hermione?\rdblquote  asked McLaggen, forcing his way through the throng a minute later.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, sorry,\rdblquote  said Harry, and he turned quickly to join in Luna\rquote s conversation, forgetting for a split second to whom she was talking.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter!\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney in deep, vibrant tones, noticing him for the first time.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, hello,\rdblquote  said Harry unenthusiastically.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My dear boy!\rdblquote  she said in a very carrying whisper. \ldblquote The rumors! The stories! \lquote The Chosen One\rquote ! Of course, I have known for a very long time. \'85 The omens were never good, Harry. \'85 But why\lang3081  \lang1033 have you not returned to Divination? For you, of all people, the subject is of the utmost importance!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ah, Sybill, we all think our subject\rquote s most important!\rdblquote  said a loud voice, and Slughorn appeared at Professor Trelawney\rquote s other side, his face very red, his velvet hat a little askew, a glass of mead in one hand and an enormous mince pie in the other. \ldblquote But I don\rquote t think I\rquote ve ever known such a natural at Potions!\rdblquote  said Slughorn, re\-garding Harry with a fond, if bloodshot, eye. \ldblquote Instinctive, you know \emdash  like his mother! I\rquote ve only ever taught a few with this kind of ability, I can tell you that, Sybill \emdash  why even Severus \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And to Harry\rquote s horror, Slughorn threw out an arm and seemed to scoop Snape out of thin air toward them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stop skulking and come and join us, Severus!\rdblquote  hiccuped Slughorn happily. \ldblquote I was just talking about Harry\rquote s exceptional po\-tion-making! Some credit must go to you, of course, you taught him for five years!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Trapped, with Slughorn\rquote s arm around his shoulders, Snape looked down his hooked nose at Harry, his black eyes narrowed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Funny, I never had the impression that I managed to teach Potter anything at all.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, then, it\rquote s natural ability!\rdblquote  shouted Slughorn. \ldblquote You should have seen what he gave me, first lesson, Draught of Living Death \emdash  never had a student produce finer on a first attempt, I don\rquote t think even you, Severus \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Really?\rdblquote  said Snape quietly, his eyes still boring into Harry, who felt a certain disquiet. The last thing he wanted was for Snape to start investigating the source of his newfound brilliance at Potions.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Remind me what other subjects you\rquote re taking, Harry?\rdblquote  asked Slughorn.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Defense Against the Dark Arts, Charms, Transfiguration, Herbology\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All the subjects required, in short, for an Auror,\rdblquote  said Snape, with the faintest sneer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, well, that\rquote s what I\rquote d like to do,\rdblquote  said Harry defiantly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And a great one you\rquote ll make too!\rdblquote  boomed Slughorn.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t think you should be an Auror, Harry,\rdblquote  said Luna unex\-pectedly. Everybody looked at her. \ldblquote The Aurors are part of the Rotfang Conspiracy, I thought everyone knew that. They\rquote re work\-ing to bring down the Ministry of Magic from within using a com\-bination of Dark Magic and gum disease.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry inhaled half his mead up his nose as he started to laugh. Really, it had been worth bringing Luna just for this. Emerging from his goblet, coughing, sopping wet but still grinning, he saw something calculated to raise his spirits even higher: Draco Malfoy being dragged by the ear toward them by Argus Filch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Professor Slughorn,\rdblquote  wheezed Filch, his jowls aquiver and the maniacal light of mischief-detection in his bulging eyes, \ldblquote I discov\-ered this boy lurking in an upstairs corridor. He claims to have been invited to your party and to have been delayed in setting out. Did you issue him with an invitation?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy pulled himself free of Filch\rquote s grip, looking furious.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right, I wasn\rquote t invited!\rdblquote  he said angrily. \ldblquote I was trying to gate\-crash, happy?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I\rquote m not!\rdblquote  said Filch, a statement at complete odds with the glee on his face. \ldblquote You\rquote re in trouble, you are! Didn\rquote t the headmaster say that nighttime prowling\rquote s out, unless you\rquote ve got permission, didn\rquote t he, eh?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s all right, Argus, that\rquote s all right,\rdblquote  said Slughorn, waving a\lang3081  \lang1033 hand. \ldblquote It\rquote s Christmas, and it\rquote s not a crime to want to come to a party. Just this once, we\rquote ll forget any punishment; you may stay, Draco.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Filch\rquote s expression of outraged disappointment was perfectly pre\-dictable; but why, Harry wondered, watching him, did Malfoy look almost equally unhappy? And why was Snape looking at Mal\-foy as though both angry and \'85 was it possible? \'85 a little afraid?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But almost before Harry had registered what he had seen, Filch had turned and shuffled away, muttering under his breath; Malfoy had composed his face into a smile and was thanking Slughorn for his generosity, and Snape\rquote s face was smoothly inscrutable again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s nothing, nothing,\rdblquote  said Slughorn, waving away Malfoy\rquote s thanks. \ldblquote I did know your grandfather, after all. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He always spoke very highly of you, sir,\rdblquote  said Malfoy quickly. \ldblquote Said you were the best potion-maker he\rquote d ever known. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared at Malfoy. It was not the sucking-up that intrigued him; he had watched Malfoy do that to Snape for a long time. It was the fact that Malfoy did, after all, look a little ill. This was the first time he had seen Malfoy close up for ages; he now saw that Malfoy had dark shadows under his eyes and a distinctly grayish tinge to his skin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote d like a word with you, Draco,\rdblquote  said Snape suddenly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, now, Severus,\rdblquote  said Slughorn, hiccuping again, \ldblquote it\rquote s Christ\-mas, don\rquote t be too hard \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m his Head of House, and I shall decide how hard, or other\-wise, to be,\rdblquote  said Snape curtly. \ldblquote Follow me, Draco.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They left, Snape leading the way, Malfoy looking resentful. Harry stood there for a moment, irresolute, then said, \ldblquote I\rquote ll be back in a bit, Luna \emdash  er \emdash  bathroom.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right,\rdblquote  she said cheerfully, and he thought he heard her, as he hurried off into the crowd, resume the subject of the Rotfang Conspiracy with Professor Trelawney, who seemed sincerely inter\-ested.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was easy, once out of the party, to pull his Invisibility Cloak out of his pocket and throw it over himself, for the corridor was quite deserted. What was more difficult was finding Snape and Malfoy. Harry ran down the corridor, the noise of his feet masked by the music and loud talk still issuing from Slughorn\rquote s office be\-hind him. Perhaps Snape had taken Malfoy to his office in the dun\-geons \'85 or perhaps he was escorting him back to the Slytherin common room. \'85 Harry pressed his ear against door after door as he dashed down the corridor until, with a great jolt of excitement, he crouched down to the keyhole of the last classroom in the corri\-dor and heard voices.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 cannot afford mistakes, Draco, because if you are ex\-pelled \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I didn\rquote t have anything to do with it, all right?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I hope you are telling the truth, because it was both clumsy and foolish. Already you are suspected of having a hand in it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who suspects me?\rdblquote  said Malfoy angrily. \ldblquote For the last time, I didn\rquote t do it, okay? That Bell girl must\rquote ve had an enemy no one knows about \emdash  don\rquote t look at me like that! I know what you\rquote re do\-ing, I\rquote m not stupid, but it won\rquote t work \emdash  I can stop you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a pause and then Snape said quietly, \ldblquote Ah \'85 Aunt Bellatrix has been teaching you Occlumency, I see. What thoughts are you trying to conceal from your master, Draco?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not trying to conceal anything from \i him,\i0  I just don\rquote t want \i you\i0  butting in!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry pressed his ear still more closely against the keyhole. \'85 What had happened to make Malfoy speak to Snape like this \emdash  Snape, toward whom he had always shown respect, even liking?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So that is why you have been avoiding me this term? You have feared my interference? You realize that, had anybody else failed to come to my office when I had told them repeatedly to be there, Draco \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So put me in detention! Report me to Dumbledore!\rdblquote  jeered Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was another pause. Then Snape said, \ldblquote You know perfectly well that I do not wish to do either of those things.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote d better stop telling me to come to your office then!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Listen to me,\rdblquote  said Snape, his voice so low now that Harry had to push his ear very hard against the keyhole to hear. \ldblquote I am trying to help you. I swore to your mother I would protect you. I made the Unbreakable Vow, Draco \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Looks like you\rquote ll have to break it, then, because I don\rquote t need your protection! It\rquote s my job, he gave it to me and I\rquote m doing it, I\rquote ve got a plan and it\rquote s going to work, it\rquote s just taking a bit longer than I thought it would!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is your plan?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s none of your business!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you tell me what you are trying to do, I can assist you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve got all the assistance I need, thanks, I\rquote m not alone!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You were certainly alone tonight, which was foolish in the ex\-treme, wandering the corridors without lookouts or backup, these are elementary mistakes \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I would\rquote ve had Crabbe and Goyle with me if you hadn\rquote t put them in detention!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Keep your voice down!\rdblquote  spat Snape, for Malfoy\rquote s voice had risen excitedly. \ldblquote If your friends Crabbe and Goyle intend to pass their Defense Against the Dark Arts O.W.L. this time around, they will need to work a little harder than they are doing at pres \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What does it matter?\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote Defense Against the Dark Arts \emdash  it\rquote s all just a joke, isn\rquote t it, an act? Like any of us need pro\-tecting against the Dark Arts \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It is an act that is crucial to success, Draco!\rdblquote  said Snape. \ldblquote Where do you think I would have been all these years, if I had not known how to act? Now listen to me! You are being incautious, wandering around at night, getting yourself caught, and if you are placing your reliance in assistants like Crabbe and Goyle \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They\rquote re not the only ones, I\rquote ve got other people on my side, better people!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then why not confide in me, and I can \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know what you\rquote re up to! You want to steal my glory!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was another pause, then Snape said coldly, \ldblquote You are speaking like a child. I quite understand that your father\rquote s capture and imprisonment has upset you, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had barely a second\rquote s warning; he heard Malfoy\rquote s footsteps on the other side of the door and flung himself out of the way just as it burst open; Malfoy was striding away down the corridor, past the open door of Slughorn\rquote s office, around the distant corner, and out of sight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hardly daring to breathe, Harry remained crouched down as Snape emerged slowly from the classroom. His expression unfath\-omable, he returned to the party. Harry remained on the floor, hid\-den beneath the cloak, his mind racing.\lang3081\par
