\lang1033\ldblquote Hmm \'85 did either of them actually mention Voldemort\rquote s name?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry frowned, trying to remember. \ldblquote I\rquote m not sure \'85 Snape definitely said \lquote your master,\rquote  and who else would that be?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know,\rdblquote  said Hermione, biting her lip. \ldblquote Maybe his father?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She stared across the room, apparently lost in thought, not even noticing Lavender tickling Ron. \ldblquote How\rquote s Lupin?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not great,\rdblquote  said Harry, and he told her all about Lupin\rquote s mission among the werewolves and the difficulties he was facing. \ldblquote Have you heard of this Fenrir Greyback?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, I have!\rdblquote  said Hermione, sounding startled. \ldblquote And so have you, Harry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote When, History of Magic? You know full well I never lis\-tened \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, no, not History of Magic \emdash  Malfoy threatened Borgin with him!\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Back in Knockturn Alley, don\rquote t you re\-member? He told Borgin that Greyback was an old family friend and that he\rquote d be checking up on Borgin\rquote s progress!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry gaped at her. \ldblquote I forgot! But this \i proves\i0  Malfoy\rquote s a Death Eater, how else could he be in contact with Greyback and telling him what to do?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It is pretty suspicious,\rdblquote  breathed Hermione. \ldblquote Unless \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, come on,\rdblquote  said Harry in exasperation, \ldblquote you can\rquote t get round this one!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 there is the possibility it was an empty threat.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re unbelievable, you are,\rdblquote  said Harry, shaking his head. \ldblquote We\rquote ll see who\rquote s right. \'85 You\rquote ll be eating your words, Hermione,\lang3081  \lang1033 just like the Ministry. Oh yeah, I had a row with Rufus Scrimgeour as well. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And the rest of the evening passed amicably with both of them abusing the Minister of Magic, for Hermione, like Ron, thought that after all the Ministry had put Harry through the previous year, they had a great deal of nerve asking him for help now.\lang3081\par
