\lang1033 The lamps in Dumbledore\rquote s office were lit, the portraits of pre\-vious headmasters were snoring gently in their frames, and the Pen\-sieve was ready upon the desk once more. Dumbledore\rquote s hands lay on either side of it, the right one as blackened and burnt-looking as ever. It did not seem to have healed at all and Harry wondered, for perhaps the hundredth time, what had caused such a distinctive in\-jury, but did not ask; Dumbledore had said that he would know eventually and there was, in any case, another subject he wanted to discuss. But before Harry could say anything about Snape and Malfoy, Dumbledore spoke.\lang3081\par
