Patches of bright blue sky were beginning to appear over the castle turrets, but these signs of approaching summer did not lift Harry\rquote s mood. He had been thwarted, both in his attempts to find out what Malfoy was doing, and in his efforts to start a conver\-sation with Slughorn that might lead, somehow, to Slughorn hand\-ing over the memory he had apparently suppressed for decades.\par
\ldblquote For the last time, just forget about Malfoy,\rdblquote  Hermione told Harry firmly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were sitting with Ron in a sunny corner of the courtyard after lunch. Hermione and Ron were both clutching a Ministry of Magic leaflet \emdash  \i Common Apparition Mistakes and How to Avoid Them\i0  \emdash  for they were taking their tests that very afternoon, but by and large the leaflets had not proved soothing to the nerves.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron gave a start and tried to hide behind Hermione as a girl came around the corner.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It isn\rquote t Lavender,\rdblquote  said Hermione wearily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, good,\rdblquote  said Ron, relaxing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter?\rdblquote  said the girl. \ldblquote I was asked to give you this.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thanks \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart sank as he took the small scroll of parchment. Once the girl was out of earshot he said, \ldblquote Dumbledore said we wouldn\rquote t be having any more lessons until I got the memory!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Maybe he wants to check on how you\rquote re doing?\rdblquote  suggested Hermione, as Harry unrolled the parchment; but rather than find\-ing Dumbledore\rquote s long, narrow, slanted writing he saw an untidy sprawl, very difficult to read due to the presence of large blotches on the parchment where the ink had run.\par
\par
