\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, but for something like this?\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote We\rquote ve risked a lot to help Hagrid out, but after all \emdash  Aragog\rquote s dead. If it were a question of saving him \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  I\rquote d want to go even less,\rdblquote  said Ron firmly. \ldblquote You didn\rquote t meet him, Hermione. Believe me, being dead will have improved him a lot.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry took the note back and stared down at all the inky blotches all over it. Tears had clearly fallen thick and fast upon the parchment. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, you \i can\rquote t\i0  be thinking of going,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote It\rquote s such a pointless thing to get detention for.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry sighed. \ldblquote Yeah, I know,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote I s\rquote pose Hagrid\rquote ll have to bury Aragog without us.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, he will,\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking relieved. \ldblquote Look, Potions will be almost empty this afternoon, with us all off doing our tests. \'85 Try and soften Slughorn up a bit then!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fifty-seventh time lucky, you think?\rdblquote  said Harry bitterly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lucky,\rdblquote  said Ron suddenly. \ldblquote Harry, that\rquote s it \emdash  get lucky!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What d\rquote you mean?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Use your lucky potion!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, that\rquote s \emdash  that\rquote s it!\rdblquote  said Hermione, sounding stunned. \ldblquote Of course! Why didn\rquote t I think of it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
