\lang1033\ldblquote What was the werewolf\rquote s name?\rdblquote  said Harry quickly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, the rumor is that it was that Fenrir Greyback,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I knew it \emdash  the maniac who likes attacking kids, the one Lupin told me about!\rdblquote  said Harry angrily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione looked at him bleakly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, you\rquote ve got to get that memory,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote It\rquote s all about stopping Voldemort, isn\rquote t it? These dreadful things that are hap\-pening are all down to him. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The bell rang overhead in the castle and both Hermione and Ron jumped to their feet, looking terrified.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ll do fine,\rdblquote  Harry told them both, as they headed toward the entrance hall to meet the rest of the people taking their Ap\-parition Test. \ldblquote Good luck.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And you too!\rdblquote  said Hermione with a significant look, as Harry headed off to the dungeons.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There were only three of them in Potions that afternoon: Harry, Ernie, and Draco Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All too young to Apparate just yet?\rdblquote  said Slughorn genially. \ldblquote Not turned seventeen yet?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They shook their heads.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ah well,\rdblquote  said Slughorn cheerily, \ldblquote as we\rquote re so few, we\rquote ll do some\-thing \i fun.\i0  I want you all to brew me up something amusing!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That sounds good, sir,\rdblquote  said Ernie sycophantically, rubbing his hands together. Malfoy, on the other hand, did not crack a smile.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What do you mean, \lquote something amusing\rquote ?\rdblquote  he said irritably.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, surprise me,\rdblquote  said Slughorn airily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy opened his copy of \i Advanced Potion-Making\i0  with a sulky expression. It could not have been plainer that he thought this les\-son was a waste of time. Undoubtedly, Harry thought, watching him over the top of his own book, Malfoy was begrudging the time he could otherwise be spending in the Room of Requirement.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Was it his imagination, or did Malfoy, like Tonks, look thinner? Certainly he looked paler; his skin still had that grayish tinge, probably because he so rarely saw daylight these days. But there was no air of smugness, excitement, or superiority; none of the swagger that he had had on the Hogwarts Express, when he had boasted openly of the mission he had been given by Voldemort. \'85 There could be only one conclusion, in Harry\rquote s opinion: The mission, whatever it was, was going badly.\lang3081\par
