\lang1033\ldblquote Liked her?\rdblquote  said Slughorn, his eyes brimming with tears once more. \ldblquote I don\rquote t imagine anyone who met her wouldn\rquote t have liked her. \'85 Very brave \'85 Very funny \'85 It was the most horrible thing. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But you won\rquote t help her son,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote She gave me her life, but you won\rquote t give me a memory.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid\rquote s rumbling snores filled the cabin. Harry looked steadily into Slughorn\rquote s tear-filled eyes. The Potions master seemed unable to look away.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t say that,\rdblquote  he whispered. \ldblquote It isn\rquote t a question \'85 If it were to help you, of course \'85 but no purpose can be served \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It can,\rdblquote  said Harry clearly. \ldblquote Dumbledore needs information. I need information.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He knew he was safe: Felix was telling him that Slughorn would remember nothing of this in the morning. Looking Slughorn straight in the eye, Harry leaned forward a little.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I am the Chosen One. I have to kill him. I need that memory.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn turned paler than ever; his shiny forehead gleamed with sweat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You \i are\i0  the Chosen One?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course I am,\rdblquote  said Harry calmly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But then \'85 my dear boy \'85 you\rquote re asking a great deal \'85 you\rquote re asking me, in fact, to aid you in your attempt to destroy \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You don\rquote t want to get rid of the wizard who killed Lily Evans?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, Harry, of course I do, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re scared he\rquote ll find out you helped me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn said nothing; he looked terrified.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Be brave like my mother, Professor. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slughorn raised a pudgy hand and pressed his shaking fingers to his mouth; he looked for a moment like an enormously overgrown baby.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I am not proud \'85\rdblquote  he whispered through his fingers. \ldblquote I am ashamed of what \emdash  of what that memory shows. \'85 I think I may have done great damage that day. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote d cancel out anything you did by giving me the memory,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote It would be a very brave and noble thing to do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid twitched in his sleep and snored on. Slughorn and Harry stared at each other over the guttering candle. There was a long, long silence, but Felix Felicis told Harry not to break it, to wait.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then, very slowly, Slughorn put his hand in his pocket and pulled out his wand. He put his other hand inside his cloak and took out a small, empty bottle. Still looking into Harry\rquote s eyes,\lang3081  \lang1033 Slughorn touched the tip of his wand to his temple and withdrew it, so that a long, silver thread of memory came away too, clinging to the wand tip. Longer and longer the memory stretched until it broke and swung, silvery bright, from the wand. Slughorn lowered it into the bottle where it coiled, then spread, swirling like gas. He corked the bottle with a trembling hand and then passed it across the table to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thank you very much, Professor.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re a good boy,\rdblquote  said Professor Slughorn, tears trickling down his fat cheeks into his walrus mustache. \ldblquote And you\rquote ve got her eyes. \'85 Just don\rquote t think too badly of me once you\rquote ve seen it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he too put his head on his arms, gave a deep sigh, and fell asleep.\lang3081\par
