Exhausted but delighted with his night\rquote s work, Harry told Ron and Hermione everything that had happened during next morning\rquote s Charms lesson (having first cast the \i Muffliato\i0  spell upon those nearest them). They were both satisfyingly impressed by the way he had wheedled the memory out of Slughorn and pos\-itively awed when he told them about Voldemort\rquote s Horcruxes and Dumbledore\rquote s promise to take Harry along, should he find an\-other one.\par
\ldblquote Wow,\rdblquote  said Ron, when Harry had finally finished telling them everything; Ron was waving his wand very vaguely in the direction of the ceiling without paying the slightest bit of attention to what he was doing. \ldblquote Wow. You\rquote re actually going to go with Dumbledore \'85 and try and destroy \'85 wow.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, you\rquote re making it snow,\rdblquote  said Hermione patiently, grab\-bing his wrist and redirecting his wand away from the ceiling from which, sure enough, large white flakes had started to fall. Lavender\lang3081  \lang1033 Brown, Harry noticed, glared at Hermione from a neighboring table through very red eyes, and Hermione immediately let go of Ron\rquote s arm.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yeah,\rdblquote  said Ron, looking down at his shoulders in vague surprise. \ldblquote Sorry \'85 looks like we\rquote ve all got horrible dandruff now. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He brushed some of the fake snow off Hermione\rquote s shoulder. Lavender burst into tears. Ron looked immensely guilty and turned his back on her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We split up,\rdblquote  he told Harry out of the corner of his mouth. \ldblquote Last night. When she saw me coming out of the dormitory with Hermione. Obviously she couldn\rquote t see you, so she thought it had just been the two of us.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ah,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Well \emdash  you don\rquote t mind it\rquote s over, do you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  Ron admitted. \ldblquote It was pretty bad while she was yelling, but at least I didn\rquote t have to finish it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Coward,\rdblquote  said Hermione, though she looked amused. \ldblquote Well, it was a bad night for romance all around. Ginny and Dean split up too, Harry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry thought there was a rather knowing look in her eye as she told him that, but she could not possibly know that his insides were suddenly dancing the conga. Keeping his face as immobile and his voice as indifferent as he could, he asked, \ldblquote How come?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, something really silly \'85 She said he was always trying to help her through the portrait hole, like she couldn\rquote t climb in her\-self\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 but they\rquote ve been a bit rocky for ages.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry glanced over at Dean on the other side of the classroom. He certainly looked unhappy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, this puts you in a bit of a dilemma, doesn\rquote t it?\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What d\rquote you mean?\rdblquote  said Harry quickly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Quidditch team,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote If Ginny and Dean aren\rquote t speaking \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \emdash  oh yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Flitwick,\rdblquote  said Ron in a warning tone. The tiny little Charms master was bobbing his way toward them, and Hermione was the only one who had managed to turn vinegar into wine; her glass flask was full of deep crimson liquid, whereas the contents of Harry\rquote s and Ron\rquote s were still murky brown.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Now, now, boys,\rdblquote  squeaked Professor Flitwick reproachfully. \ldblquote A little less talk, a little more action \'85 Let me see you try. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Together they raised their wands, concentrating with all their might, and pointed them at their flasks. Harry\rquote s vinegar turned to ice; Ron\rquote s flask exploded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 for homework,\rdblquote  said Professor Flitwick, reemerging from under the table and pulling shards of glass out of the top of his hat, \ldblquote\i practice.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had one of their rare joint free periods after Charms and walked back to the common room together. Ron seemed to be pos\-itively lighthearted about the end of his relationship with Laven\-der, and Hermione seemed cheery too, though when asked what she was grinning about she simply said, \ldblquote It\rquote s a nice day.\rdblquote  Neither of them seemed to have noticed that a fierce battle was raging inside Harry\rquote s brain:\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i She\rquote s Ron\rquote s sister.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 But she\rquote s ditched Dean!\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i She\rquote s still Ron\rquote s sister.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 I\rquote m his best mate!\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i That\rquote ll make it worse.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 If I talked to him first \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i He\rquote d hit you.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 What if I don\rquote t care?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i He\rquote s your best mate\i0 !\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry barely noticed that they were climbing through the por\-trait hole into the sunny common room, and only vaguely regis\-tered the small group of seventh years clustered together there, until Hermione cried, \ldblquote Katie! You\rquote re back! Are you okay?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared: It was indeed Katie Bell, looking completely healthy and surrounded by her jubilant friends.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m really well!\rdblquote  she said happily. \ldblquote They let me out of St. Mungo\rquote s on Monday, I had a couple of days at home with Mum and Dad and then came back here this morning. Leanne was just telling me about McLaggen and the last match, Harry. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote well, now you\rquote re back and Ron\rquote s fit, we\rquote ll have a decent chance of thrashing Ravenclaw, which means we could still be in the running for the Cup. Listen, Katie \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had to put the question to her at once; his curiosity even drove Ginny temporarily from his brain. He dropped his voice as Katie\rquote s friends started gathering up their things; apparently they were late for Transfiguration.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 that necklace \'85 can you remember who gave it to you now?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Katie, shaking her head ruefully. \ldblquote Everyone\rquote s been asking me, but I haven\rquote t got a clue. The last thing I remember was walking into the ladies\rquote  in the Three Broomsticks.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You definitely went into the bathroom, then?\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I know I pushed open the door,\rdblquote  said Katie, \ldblquote so I suppose whoever Imperiused me was standing just behind it. After that, my memory\rquote s a blank until about two weeks ago in St. Mungo\rquote s. Listen, I\rquote d better go, I wouldn\rquote t put it past McGonagall to give me lines even if it is my first day back. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
