\lang1033\ldblquote As though it was celebrating?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Most definitely.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then I called out \lquote Who\rquote s there?\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You couldn\rquote t have found out who it was without asking?\rdblquote  Harry asked her, slightly frustrated.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Inner Eye,\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney with dignity, straight\-ening her shawls and many strands of glittering beads, \ldblquote was fixed upon matters well outside the mundane realms of whooping voices.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  said Harry hastily; he had heard about Professor Trelawney\rquote s Inner Eye all too often before. \ldblquote And did the voice say who was there?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, it did not,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote Everything went pitch-black and the next thing I knew, I was being hurled headfirst out of the room!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And you didn\rquote t see that coming?\rdblquote  said Harry, unable to help himself.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I did not, as I say, it was pitch \emdash\rdblquote  She stopped and glared at him suspiciously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think you\rquote d better tell Professor Dumbledore,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote He ought to know Malfoy\rquote s celebrating \emdash  I mean, that someone threw you out of the room.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 To his surprise, Professor Trelawney drew herself up at this sug\-gestion, looking haughty.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The headmaster has intimated that he would prefer fewer visits from me,\rdblquote  she said coldly. \ldblquote I am not one to press my company upon those who do not value it. If Dumbledore chooses to ignore the warnings the cards show \emdash\rdblquote  Her bony hand closed suddenly around Harry\rquote s wrist. \ldblquote Again and again, no matter how I lay them out \emdash\rdblquote  And she pulled a card dramatically from underneath her shawls. \ldblquote\emdash  the lightning-struck tower,\rdblquote  she whispered. \ldblquote Calamity. Disaster. Coming nearer all the time \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  said Harry again. \ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I still think you should tell Dumbledore about this voice, and everything going dark and being thrown out of the room. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You think so?\rdblquote  Professor Trelawney seemed to consider the matter for a moment, but Harry could tell that she liked the idea of retelling her little adventure.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m going to see him right now,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote I\rquote ve got a meeting with him. We could go together.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, well, in that case,\rdblquote  said Professor Trelawney with a smile. She bent down, scooped up her sherry bottles, and dumped them unceremoniously in a large blue-and-white vase standing in a nearby niche.\lang3081\par
