Harry could smell salt and hear rushing waves; a light, chilly breeze ruffled his hair as he looked out at moon\-lit sea and star-strewn sky. He was standing upon a high outcrop of dark rock, water foaming and churning below him. He glanced over his shoulder. A towering cliff stood behind them, a sheer drop, black and faceless. A few large chunks of rock, such as the one upon which Harry and Dumbledore were standing, looked as though they had broken away from the cliff face at some point in the past. It was a bleak, harsh view, the sea and the rock unrelieved by any tree or sweep of grass or sand.\par
\ldblquote What do you think?\rdblquote  asked Dumbledore. He might have been asking Harry\rquote s opinion on whether it was a good site for a picnic.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They brought the kids from the orphanage here?\rdblquote  asked Harry, who could not imagine a less cozy spot for a day trip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not here, precisely,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote There is a village of sorts about halfway along the cliffs behind us. I believe the orphans\lang3081  \lang1033 were taken there for a little sea air and a view of the waves. No, I think it was only ever Tom Riddle and his youthful victims who visited this spot. No Muggle could reach this rock unless they were uncommonly good mountaineers, and boats cannot approach the cliffs, the waters around them are too dangerous. I imagine that Riddle climbed down; magic would have served better than ropes. And he brought two small children with him, probably for the pleasure of terrorizing them. I think the journey alone would have done it, don\rquote t you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked up at the cliff again and felt goose bumps.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But his final destination \emdash  and ours \emdash  lies a little farther on. Come.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore beckoned Harry to the very edge of the rock where a series of jagged niches made footholds leading down to boulders that lay half-submerged in water and closer to the cliff. It was a treacherous descent and Dumbledore, hampered slightly by his withered hand, moved slowly. The lower rocks were slippery with seawater. Harry could feel flecks of cold salt spray hitting his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Lumos,\i0\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, as he reached the boulder closest to the cliff face. A thousand flecks of golden light sparkled upon the dark surface of the water a few feet below where he crouched; the black wall of rock beside him was illuminated too.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You see?\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly, holding his wand a little higher. Harry saw a fissure in the cliff into which dark water was swirling.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You will not object to getting a little wet?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then take off your Invisibility Cloak \emdash  there is no need for it now \emdash  and let us take the plunge.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And with the sudden agility of a much younger man, Dumble\-dore slid from the boulder, landed in the sea, and began to swim, with a perfect breaststroke, toward the dark slit in the rock face, his lit wand held in his teeth. Harry pulled off his cloak, stuffed it into his pocket, and followed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The water was icy; Harry\rquote s waterlogged clothes billowed around him and weighed him down. Taking deep breaths that filled his nostrils with the tang of salt and seaweed, he struck out for the shimmering, shrinking light now moving deeper into the cliff.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The fissure soon opened into a dark tunnel that Harry could tell would be filled with water at high tide. The slimy walls were barely three feet apart and glimmered like wet tar in the passing light of Dumbledore\rquote s wand. A little way in, the passageway curved to the left, and Harry saw that it extended far into the cliff. He continued to swim in Dumbledore\rquote s wake, the tips of his benumbed fingers brushing the rough, wet rock.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then he saw Dumbledore rising out of the water ahead, his sil\-ver hair and dark robes gleaming. When Harry reached the spot he found steps that led into a large cave. He clambered up them, water streaming from his soaking clothes, and emerged, shivering uncontrollably, into the still and freezing air.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore was standing in the middle of the cave, his wand held high as he turned slowly on the spot, examining the walls and ceiling.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, this is the place,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How can you tell?\rdblquote  Harry spoke in a whisper.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It has known magic,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore simply.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could not tell whether the shivers he was experiencing were due to his spine-deep coldness or to the same awareness of\lang3081  \lang1033 enchantments. He watched as Dumbledore continued to revolve on the spot, evidently concentrating on things Harry could not see.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is merely the antechamber, the entrance hall,\rdblquote  said Dum\-bledore after a moment or two. \ldblquote We need to penetrate the inner place. \'85 Now it is Lord Voldemort\rquote s obstacles that stand in our way, rather than those nature made. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore approached the wall of the cave and caressed it with his blackened fingertips, murmuring words in a strange tongue that Harry did not understand. Twice Dumbledore walked right around the cave, touching as much of the rough rock as he could, occasionally pausing, running his fingers backward and for\-ward over a particular spot, until finally he stopped, his hand pressed flat against the wall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Here,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote We go on through here. The entrance is con\-cealed.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not ask how Dumbledore knew. He had never seen a wizard work things out like this, simply by looking and touching; but Harry had long since learned that bangs and smoke were more often the marks of ineptitude than expertise.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore stepped back from the cave wall and pointed his wand at the rock. For a moment, an arched outline appeared there, blazing white as though there was a powerful light behind the crack.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ve d-done it!\rdblquote  said Harry through chattering teeth, but be\-fore the words had left his lips the outline had gone, leaving the rock as bare and solid as ever. Dumbledore looked around.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, I\rquote m so sorry, I forgot,\rdblquote  he said; he now pointed his wand at Harry and at once, Harry\rquote s clothes were as warm and dry as if they had been hanging in front of a blazing fire.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thank you,\rdblquote  said Harry gratefully, but Dumbledore had al\-ready turned his attention back to the solid cave wall. He did not try any more magic, but simply stood there staring at it intently, as though something extremely interesting was written on it. Harry stayed quite still; he did not want to break Dumbledore\rquote s concen\-tration. Then, after two solid minutes, Dumbledore said quietly, \ldblquote Oh, surely not. So crude.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is it, Professor?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I rather think,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, putting his uninjured hand inside his robes and drawing out a short silver knife of the kind Harry used to chop potion ingredients, \ldblquote that we are required to make payment to pass.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Payment?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote You\rquote ve got to give the door something?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
