\lang1033 As they flew over the dark, twisting lane down which they had walked earlier, Harry heard, over the whistling of the night air in his ears, Dumbledore muttering in some strange language again. He thought he understood why as he felt his broom shudder when they flew over the boundary wall into the grounds: Dumbledore was undoing the enchantments he himself had set around the cas\-tle so they could enter at speed. The Dark Mark was glittering di\-rectly above the Astronomy Tower, the highest of the castle. Did that mean the death had occurred there?\lang3081\par
