\lang1033 Malfoy merely stared at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I see,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore kindly, when Malfoy neither moved nor spoke. \ldblquote You are afraid to act until they join you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not afraid!\rdblquote  snarled Malfoy, though he still made no move to hurt Dumbledore. \ldblquote It\rquote s you who should be scared!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But why? I don\rquote t think you will kill me, Draco. Killing is not nearly as easy as the innocent believe. \'85 So tell me, while we wait for your friends \'85 how did you smuggle them in here? It seems to have taken you a long time to work out how to do it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy looked as though he was fighting down the urge to shout, or to vomit. He gulped and took several deep breaths, glar\-ing at Dumbledore, his wand pointing directly at the latter\rquote s heart. Then, as though he could not help himself, he said, \ldblquote I had to mend that broken Vanishing Cabinet that no one\rquote s used for years. The one Montague got lost in last year.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Aaaah.\rdblquote  Dumbledore\rquote s sigh was half a groan. He closed his eyes for a moment. \ldblquote That was clever. \'85 There is a pair, I take it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote In Borgin and Burkes,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, \ldblquote and they make a kind of passage between them. Montague told me that when he was stuck in the Hogwarts one, he was trapped in limbo but sometimes he could hear what was going on at school, and sometimes what was going on in the shop, as if the cabinet was traveling between them, but he couldn\rquote t make anyone hear him. \'85 In the end, he managed to Apparate out, even though he\rquote d never passed his test. He nearly died doing it. Everyone thought it was a really good story, but I was the only one who realized what it meant \emdash  even Borgin didn\rquote t know \emdash  I was the one who realized there could be a way into Hog\-warts through the cabinets if I fixed the broken one.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very good,\rdblquote  murmured Dumbledore. \ldblquote So the Death Eaters were able to pass from Borgin and Burkes into the school to help you. \'85 A clever plan, a very clever plan \'85 and, as you say, right under my nose.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, who bizarrely seemed to draw courage and comfort from Dumbledore\rquote s praise. \ldblquote Yeah, it was!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But there were times,\rdblquote  Dumbledore went on, \ldblquote weren\rquote t there, when you were not sure you would succeed in mending the cabi\-net? And you resorted to crude and badly judged measures such as sending me a cursed necklace that was bound to reach the wrong hands \'85 poisoning mead there was only the slightest chance I might drink. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, well, you still didn\rquote t realize who was behind that stuff, did you?\rdblquote  sneered Malfoy, as Dumbledore slid a little down the ram\-parts, the strength in his legs apparently fading, and Harry strug\-gled fruitlessly, mutely, against the enchantment binding him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote As a matter of fact, I did,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote I was sure it was you.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why didn\rquote t you stop me, then?\rdblquote  Malfoy demanded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I tried, Draco. Professor Snape has been keeping watch over you on my orders \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He hasn\rquote t been doing \i your\i0  orders, he promised my mother \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course that is what he would tell you, Draco, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s a double agent, you stupid old man, he isn\rquote t working for you, you just think he is!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We must agree to differ on that, Draco. It so happens that I trust Professor Snape \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, you\rquote re losing your grip, then!\rdblquote  sneered Malfoy. \ldblquote He\rquote s been offering me plenty of help \emdash  wanting all the glory for himself\emdash  wanting a bit of the action \emdash  \lquote What are you doing?\rquote  \lquote Did you do the necklace, that was stupid, it could have blown everything \emdash\rquote  But I haven\rquote t told him what I\rquote ve been doing in the Room of Re\-quirement, he\rquote s going to wake up tomorrow and it\rquote ll all be over and he won\rquote t be the Dark Lord\rquote s favorite anymore, he\rquote ll be nothing compared to me, nothing!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very gratifying,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore mildly. \ldblquote We all like appreci\-ation for our own hard work, of course. But you must have had an accomplice, all the same \'85 someone in Hogsmeade, someone who was able to slip Katie the \emdash  the \emdash  aaaah \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore closed his eyes again and nodded, as though he was about to fall asleep. \ldblquote\'85 of course \'85 Rosmerta. How long has she been under the Imperius Curse?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Got there at last, have you?\rdblquote  Malfoy taunted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was another yell from below, rather louder than the last.\lang3081  \lang1033 Malfoy looked nervously over his shoulder again, then back at Dumbledore, who went on: \ldblquote So poor Rosmerta was forced to lurk in her own bathroom and pass that necklace to any Hogwarts stu\-dent who entered the room unaccompanied? And the poisoned mead \'85 well, naturally, Rosmerta was able to poison it for you before she sent the bottle to Slughorn, believing that it was to be my Christmas present. \'85 Yes, very neat \'85 very neat \'85 Poor Mr. Filch would not, of course, think to check a bottle of Rosmer\-ta\rquote s. Tell me, how have you been communicating with Rosmerta? I thought we had all methods of communication in and out of the school monitored.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Enchanted coins,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, as though he was compelled to keep talking, though his wand hand was shaking badly. \ldblquote I had one and she had the other and I could send her messages \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Isn\rquote t that the secret method of communication the group that called themselves Dumbledore\rquote s Army used last year?\rdblquote  asked Dum\-bledore. His voice was light and conversational, but Harry saw him slip an inch lower down the wall as he said it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I got the idea from them,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, with a twisted smile. \ldblquote I got the idea of poisoning the mead from the Mudblood Granger as well, I heard her talking in the library about Filch not recognizing potions.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Please do not use that offensive word in front of me,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy gave a harsh laugh. \ldblquote You care about me saying \lquote Mud\-blood\rquote  when I\rquote m about to kill you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, I do,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, and Harry saw his feet slide a lit\-tle on the floor as he struggled to remain upright. \ldblquote But as for being\lang3081  \lang1033 about to kill me, Draco, you have had several long minutes now, we are quite alone, I am more defenseless than you can have dreamed of finding me, and still you have not acted. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy\rquote s mouth contorted involuntarily, as though he had tasted something very bitter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Now, about tonight,\rdblquote  Dumbledore went on, \ldblquote I am a little puzzled about how it happened. \'85 You knew that I had left the school? But of course,\rdblquote  he answered his own question, \ldblquote Rosmerta saw me leaving, she tipped you off using your ingenious coins, I\rquote m sure.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote But she said you were just going for a drink, you\rquote d be back. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I certainly did have a drink \'85 and I came back \'85 after a fashion,\rdblquote  mumbled Dumbledore. \ldblquote So you decided to spring a trap for me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We decided to put the Dark Mark over the tower and get you to hurry up here, to see who\rquote d been killed,\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote And it worked!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well \'85 yes and no \'85\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote But am I to take it, then, that nobody has been murdered?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Someone\rquote s dead,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, and his voice seemed to go up an octave as he said it. \ldblquote One of your people \'85 I don\rquote t know who, it was dark. \'85 I stepped over the body. \'85 I was supposed to be waiting up here when you got back, only your Phoenix lot got in the way. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, they do that,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a bang and shouts from below, louder than ever; it sounded as though people were fighting on the actual spiral stair\-case that led to where Dumbledore, Malfoy, and Harry stood, and\lang3081  \lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart thundered unheard in his invisible chest. \'85 Some\-one was dead. \'85 Malfoy had stepped over the body \'85 but who was it?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There is little time, one way or another,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote So let us discuss your options, Draco.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i My\i0  options!\rdblquote  said Malfoy loudly. \ldblquote I\rquote m standing here with a wand \emdash  I\rquote m about to kill you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My dear boy, let us have no more pretense about that. If you were going to kill me, you would have done it when you first dis\-armed me, you would not have stopped for this pleasant chat about ways and means.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I haven\rquote t got any options!\rdblquote  said Malfoy, and he was suddenly white as Dumbledore. \ldblquote I\rquote ve got to do it! He\rquote ll kill me! He\rquote ll kill my whole family!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I appreciate the difficulty of your position,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote Why else do you think I have not confronted you before now? Be\-cause I knew that you would have been murdered if Lord Volde\-mort realized that I suspected you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy winced at the sound of the name.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I did not dare speak to you of the mission with which I knew you had been entrusted, in case he used Legilimency against you,\rdblquote  continued Dumbledore. \ldblquote But now at last we can speak plainly to each other. \'85 No harm has been done, you have hurt nobody, though you are very lucky that your unintentional victims sur\-vived. \'85 I can help you, Draco.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, you can\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, his wand hand shaking very badly indeed. \ldblquote Nobody can. He told me to do it or he\rquote ll kill me. I\rquote ve got no choice.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come over to the\lang3081  \lang1033 right side, Draco, and we can hide you more completely than you can possibly imagine. What is more, I can send members of the Order to your mother tonight to hide her like\-wise. Your father is safe at the moment in Azkaban. \'85 When the time comes, we can protect him too. Come over to the right side, Draco \'85 you are not a killer. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy stared at Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But I got this far, didn\rquote t I?\rdblquote  he said slowly. \ldblquote They thought I\rquote d die in the attempt, but I\rquote m here \'85 and you\rquote re in my power. \'85 I\rquote m the one with the wand. \'85 You\rquote re at my mercy. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, Draco,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \ldblquote It is my mercy, and not yours, that matters now.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy did not speak. His mouth was open, his wand hand still trembling. Harry thought he saw it drop by a fraction \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But suddenly footsteps were thundering up the stairs, and a sec\-ond later Malfoy was buffeted out of the way as four people in black robes burst through the door onto the ramparts. Still para\-lyzed, his eyes staring unblinkingly, Harry gazed in terror upon four strangers: It seemed the Death Eaters had won the fight below.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A lumpy-looking man with an odd lopsided leer gave a wheezy giggle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore cornered!\rdblquote  he said, and he turned to a stocky little woman who looked as though she could be his sister and who was grinning eagerly. \ldblquote Dumbledore wandless, Dumbledore alone! Well done, Draco, well done!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good evening, Amycus,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore calmly, as though welcoming the man to a tea party. \ldblquote And you\rquote ve brought Alecto too. \'85 Charming \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The woman gave an angry little titter. \ldblquote Think your little jokes\rquote ll help you on your deathbed then?\rdblquote  she jeered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Jokes? No, no, these are manners,\rdblquote  replied Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Do it,\rdblquote  said the stranger standing nearest to Harry, a big, rangy man with matted gray hair and whiskers, whose black Death Eater\rquote s robes looked uncomfortably tight. He had a voice like none that Harry had ever heard: a rasping bark of a voice. Harry could smell a powerful mixture of dirt, sweat, and, unmistakably, of blood coming from him. His filthy hands had long yellowish nails.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is that you, Fenrir?\rdblquote  asked Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  rasped the other. \ldblquote Pleased to see me, Dumbledore?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I cannot say that I am.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Greyback grinned, showing pointed teeth. Blood trickled down his chin and he licked his lips slowly, obscenely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But you know how much I like kids, Dumbledore.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Am I to take it that you are attacking even without the full moon now? This is most unusual. \'85 You have developed a taste for human flesh that cannot be satisfied once a month?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Fenrir Greyback. \ldblquote Shocks you that, does it, Dumbledore? Frightens you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I cannot pretend it does not disgust me a little,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote And, yes, I am a little shocked that Draco here in\-vited you, of all people, into the school where his friends live. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I didn\rquote t,\rdblquote  breathed Malfoy. He was not looking at Fenrir; he did not seem to want to even glance at him. \ldblquote I didn\rquote t know he was go\-ing to come \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I wouldn\rquote t want to miss a trip to Hogwarts, Dumbledore,\rdblquote  rasped Greyback. \ldblquote Not when there are throats to be ripped out\'85 Delicious, delicious \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he raised a yellow fingernail and picked at his front teeth, leering at Dumbledore. \ldblquote I could do you for afters, Dumbledore.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said the fourth Death Eater sharply. He had a heavy, bru\-tal-looking face. \ldblquote We\rquote ve got orders. Draco\rquote s got to do it. Now, Draco, and quickly.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy was showing less resolution than ever. He looked terri\-fied as he stared into Dumbledore\rquote s face, which was even paler, and rather lower than usual, as he had slid so far down the rampart wall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s not long for this world anyway, if you ask me!\rdblquote  said the lopsided man, to the accompaniment of his sister\rquote s wheezing gig\-gles. \ldblquote Look at him \emdash  what\rquote s happened to you, then, Dumby?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, weaker resistance, slower reflexes, Amycus,\rdblquote  said Dumble\-dore. \ldblquote Old age, in short\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 One day, perhaps, it will happen to you \'85 if you are lucky. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s that mean, then, what\rquote s that mean?\rdblquote  yelled the Death Eater, suddenly violent. \ldblquote Always the same, weren\rquote t yeh, Dumby, talking and doing nothing, nothing. I don\rquote t even know why the Dark Lord\rquote s bothering to kill yer! Come on, Draco, do it!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But at that moment there were renewed sounds of scuffling from below and a voice shouted, \ldblquote\i They\rquote ve blocked the stairs \i0\emdash  \i Reducto\i0 ! \i REDUCTO\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart leapt: So these four had not eliminated all opposi\-tion, but merely broken through the fight to the top of the tower, and, by the sound of it, created a barrier behind them \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Now, Draco, quickly!\rdblquote  said the brutal-faced man angrily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Malfoy\rquote s hand was shaking so badly that he could barely aim.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll do it,\rdblquote  snarled Fenrir, moving toward Dumbledore with his hands outstretched, his teeth bared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I said no!\rdblquote  shouted the brutal-faced man; there was a flash of light and the werewolf was blasted out of the way; he hit the ram\-parts and staggered, looking furious. Harry\rquote s heart was hammering so hard it seemed impossible that nobody could hear him standing there, imprisoned by Dumbledore\rquote s spell \emdash  if he could only move, he could aim a curse from under the cloak \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Draco, do it or stand aside so one of us \emdash\rdblquote  screeched the woman, but at that precise moment, the door to the ramparts burst open once more and there stood Snape, his wand clutched in his hand as his black eyes swept the scene, from Dumbledore slumped against the wall, to the four Death Eaters, including the enraged werewolf, and Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ve got a problem, Snape,\rdblquote  said the lumpy Amycus, whose eyes and wand were fixed alike upon Dumbledore, \ldblquote the boy doesn\rquote t seem able \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But somebody else had spoken Snape\rquote s name, quite softly.\par
\ldblquote Severus \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The sound frightened Harry beyond anything he had experi\-enced all evening. For the first time, Dumbledore was pleading.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape said nothing, but walked forward and pushed Malfoy roughly out of the way. The three Death Eaters fell back without a word. Even the werewolf seemed cowed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape gazed for a moment at Dumbledore, and there was revul\-sion and hatred etched in the harsh lines of his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Severus \'85 please \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape raised his wand and pointed it directly at Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Avada Kedavra\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A jet of green light shot from the end of Snape\rquote s wand and hit Dumbledore squarely in the chest. Harry\rquote s scream of horror never left him; silent and unmoving, he was forced to watch as Dumble\-dore was blasted into the air. For a split second, he seemed to hang suspended beneath the shining skull, and then he fell slowly back\-ward, like a great rag doll, over the battlements and out of sight.\lang3081\par
