\lang1033\ldblquote Molly and Arthur are on their way,\rdblquote  she said, and the spell of the music was broken: Everyone roused themselves as though com\-ing out of trances, turning again to look at Bill, or else to rub their own eyes, shake their heads. \ldblquote Harry, what happened? According to Hagrid you were with Professor Dumbledore when he \emdash  when it happened. He says Professor Snape was involved in some \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Snape killed Dumbledore,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She stared at him for a moment, then swayed alarmingly; Madam Pomfrey, who seemed to have pulled herself together, ran forward, conjuring a chair from thin air, which she pushed under McGonagall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Snape,\rdblquote  repeated McGonagall faintly, falling into the chair. \ldblquote We all wondered \'85 but he trusted \'85 always \'85 \i Snape\i0  \'85 I can\rquote t believe it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Snape was a highly accomplished Occlumens,\rdblquote  said Lupin, his voice uncharacteristically harsh. \ldblquote We always knew that.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But Dumbledore swore he was on our side!\rdblquote  whispered Tonks. \ldblquote I always thought Dumbledore must know something about Snape that we didn\rquote t. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He always hinted that he had an ironclad reason for trusting Snape,\rdblquote  muttered Professor McGonagall, now dabbing at the cor\-ners of her leaking eyes with a tartan-edged handkerchief. \ldblquote I mean \'85 with Snape\rquote s history \'85 of course people were bound to won\-der \'85 but Dumbledore told me explicitly that Snape\rquote s repentance was absolutely genuine. \'85 Wouldn\rquote t hear a word against him!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote d love to know what Snape told him to convince him,\rdblquote  said Tonks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know,\rdblquote  said Harry, and they all turned to look at him. \ldblquote Snape passed Voldemort the information that made Voldemort hunt down my mum and dad. Then Snape told Dumbledore he hadn\rquote t realized what he was doing, he was really sorry he\rquote d done it, sorry that they were dead.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all stared at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And Dumbledore believed that?\rdblquote  said Lupin incredulously. \ldblquote Dumbledore believed Snape was sorry James was dead? Snape \i hated\i0  James. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And he didn\rquote t think my mother was worth a damn either,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote because she was Muggle-born. \'85 \lquote Mudblood,\rquote  he called her. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nobody asked how Harry knew this. All of them seemed to be lost in horrified shock, trying to digest the monstrous truth of what had happened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is all my fault,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall suddenly. She looked disoriented, twisting her wet handkerchief in her hands. \ldblquote My fault. I sent Filius to fetch Snape tonight, I actually sent for him to come and help us! If I hadn\rquote t alerted Snape to what was go\-ing on, he might never have joined forces with the Death Eaters. I\lang3081  \lang1033 don\rquote t think he knew they were there before Filius told him, I don\rquote t think he knew they were coming.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It isn\rquote t your fault, Minerva,\rdblquote  said Lupin firmly. \ldblquote We all wanted more help, we were glad to think Snape was on his way. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So when he arrived at the fight, he joined in on the Death Eaters\rquote  side?\rdblquote  asked Harry, who wanted every detail of Snape\rquote s du\-plicity and infamy, feverishly collecting more reasons to hate him, to swear vengeance.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know exactly how it happened,\rdblquote  said Professor McGona\-gall distractedly. \ldblquote It\rquote s all so confusing. \'85 Dumbledore had told us that he would be leaving the school for a few hours and that we were to patrol the corridors just in case \'85 Remus, Bill, and Nymphadora were to join us \'85 and so we patrolled. All seemed quiet. Every secret passageway out of the school was covered. We knew nobody could fly in. There were powerful enchantments on every entrance into the castle. I still don\rquote t know how the Death Eaters can possibly have entered. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I do,\rdblquote  said Harry, and he explained, briefly, about the pair of Vanishing Cabinets and the magical pathway they formed. \ldblquote So they got in through the Room of Requirement.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Almost against his will he glanced from Ron to Hermione, both of whom looked devastated.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I messed up, Harry,\rdblquote  said Ron bleakly. \ldblquote We did like you told us: We checked the Marauder\rquote s Map and we couldn\rquote t see Malfoy on it, so we thought he must be in the Room of Requirement, so me, Ginny, and Neville went to keep watch on it\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 but Malfoy got past us.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He came out of the room about an hour after we started\lang3081  \lang1033 keeping watch,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote He was on his own, clutching that awful shriveled arm \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote His Hand of Glory,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Gives light only to the holder, remember?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Anyway,\rdblquote  Ginny went on, \ldblquote he must have been checking whether the coast was clear to let the Death Eaters out, because the moment he saw us he threw something into the air and it all went pitch-black \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  Peruvian Instant Darkness Powder,\rdblquote  said Ron bitterly. \ldblquote Fred and George\rquote s. I\rquote m going to be having a word with them about who they let buy their products.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We tried everything, Lumos, Incendio,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote Nothing would penetrate the darkness; all we could do was grope our way out of the corridor again, and meanwhile we could hear people rushing past us. Obviously Malfoy could see because of that hand thing and was guiding them, but we didn\rquote t dare use any curses or anything in case we hit each other, and by the time we\rquote d reached a corridor that was light, they\rquote d gone.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Luckily,\rdblquote  said Lupin hoarsely, \ldblquote Ron, Ginny, and Neville ran into us almost immediately and told us what had happened. We found the Death Eaters minutes later, heading in the direction of the Astronomy Tower. Malfoy obviously hadn\rquote t expected more peo\-ple to be on the watch; he seemed to have exhausted his supply of Darkness Powder, at any rate. A fight broke out, they scattered and we gave chase. One of them, Gibbon, broke away and headed up the tower stairs \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote To set off the Mark?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He must have done, yes, they must have arranged that before they left the Room of Requirement,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote But I don\rquote t think\lang3081  \lang1033 Gibbon liked the idea of waiting up there alone for Dumbledore, because he came running back downstairs to rejoin the fight and was hit by a Killing Curse that just missed me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So if Ron was watching the Room of Requirement with Ginny and Neville,\rdblquote  said Harry, turning to Hermione, \ldblquote were you \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Outside Snape\rquote s office, yes,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione, her eyes sparkling with tears, \ldblquote with Luna. We hung around for ages outside it and nothing happened. \'85 We didn\rquote t know what was going on upstairs, Ron had taken the map. \'85 It was nearly midnight when Professor Flitwick came sprinting down into the dungeons. He was shouting about Death Eaters in the castle, I don\rquote t think he really registered that Luna and I were there at all, he just burst his way into Snape\rquote s office and we heard him saying that Snape had to go back with him and help and then we heard a loud thump and Snape came hurtling out of his room and he saw us and \emdash  and \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  Harry urged her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I was so stupid, Harry!\rdblquote  said Hermione in a high-pitched whis\-per. \ldblquote He said Professor Flitwick had collapsed and that we should go and take care of him while he \emdash  while he went to help fight the Death Eaters \emdash\rdblquote  She covered her face in shame and continued to talk into her fingers, so that her voice was muffled. \ldblquote We went into his office to see if we could help Professor Flitwick and found him unconscious on the floor \'85 and oh, it\rquote s so obvious now, Snape must have Stupefied Flitwick, but we didn\rquote t realize, Harry, we didn\rquote t realize, we just let Snape go!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s not your fault,\rdblquote  said Lupin firmly. \ldblquote Hermione, had you not obeyed Snape and got out of the way, he probably would have killed you and Luna.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So then he came upstairs,\rdblquote  said Harry, who was watching Snape\lang3081  \lang1033 running up the marble staircase in his mind\rquote s eye, his black robes billowing behind him as ever, pulling his wand from under his cloak as he ascended, \ldblquote and he found the place where you were all fighting. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We were in trouble, we were losing,\rdblquote  said Tonks in a low voice. \ldblquote Gibbon was down, but the rest of the Death Eaters seemed ready to fight to the death. Neville had been hurt, Bill had been savaged by Greyback \'85 It was all dark \'85 curses flying everywhere \'85 The Malfoy boy had vanished, he must have slipped past, up the stairs \'85 then more of them ran after him, but one of them blocked the stair behind them with some kind of curse. \'85 Neville ran at it and got thrown up into the air \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote None of us could break through,\rdblquote  said Ron, \ldblquote and that massive Death Eater was still firing off jinxes all over the place, they were bouncing off the walls and barely missing us. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then Snape was there,\rdblquote  said Tonks, \ldblquote and then he wasn\rquote t \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I saw him running toward us, but that huge Death Eater\rquote s jinx just missed me right afterward and I ducked and lost track of things,\rdblquote  said Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I saw him run straight through the cursed barrier as though it wasn\rquote t there,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote I tried to follow him, but was thrown back just like Neville. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He must have known a spell we didn\rquote t,\rdblquote  whispered McGona\-gall. \ldblquote After all \emdash  he was the Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher. \'85 I just assumed that he was in a hurry to chase after the Death Eaters who\rquote d escaped up to the tower. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He was,\rdblquote  said Harry savagely, \ldblquote but to help them, not to stop them \'85 and I\rquote ll bet you had to have a Dark Mark to get through that barrier \emdash  so what happened when he came back down?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, the big Death Eater had just fired off a hex that caused half the ceiling to fall in, and also broke the curse blocking the stairs,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote We all ran forward \emdash  those of us who were still standing anyway \emdash  and then Snape and the boy emerged out of the dust \emdash  obviously, none of us attacked them \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We just let them pass,\rdblquote  said Tonks in a hollow voice. \ldblquote We thought they were being chased by the Death Eaters \emdash  and next thing, the other Death Eaters and Greyback were back and we were fighting again \emdash  I thought I heard Snape shout something, but I don\rquote t know what \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He shouted, \lquote It\rquote s over,\rquote  \rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote He\rquote d done what he\rquote d meant to do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all fell silent. Fawkes\rquote s lament was still echoing over the dark grounds outside. As the music reverberated upon the air, un\-bidden, unwelcome thoughts slunk into Harry\rquote s mind. \'85 Had they taken Dumbledore\rquote s body from the foot of the tower yet? What would happen to it next? Where would it rest? He clenched his fists tightly in his pockets. He could feel the small cold lump of the fake Horcrux against the knuckles of his right hand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The doors of the hospital wing burst open, making them all jump: Mr. and Mrs. Weasley were striding up the ward, Fleur just behind them, her beautiful face terrified.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Molly \emdash  Arthur\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall, jumping up and hurrying to greet them. \ldblquote I am so sorry \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bill,\rdblquote  whispered Mrs. Weasley, darting past Professor McGona\-gall as she caught sight of Bill\rquote s mangled face. \ldblquote Oh, \i Bill\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin and Tonks had got up hastily and retreated so that Mr. and Mrs. Weasley could get nearer to the bed. Mrs. Weasley bent over her son and pressed her lips to his bloody forehead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You said Greyback attacked him?\rdblquote  Mr. Weasley asked Professor McGonagall distractedly. \ldblquote But he hadn\rquote t transformed? So what does that mean? What will happen to Bill?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We don\rquote t yet know,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall, looking help\-lessly at Lupin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There will probably be some contamination, Arthur,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote It is an odd case, possibly unique. \'85 We don\rquote t know what his behavior might be like when he awakens. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
