\lang1033 She let out a wail and, without waiting for the password, swung forward to admit him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As Harry had suspected it would be, the common room was jam-packed. The room fell silent as he climbed through the por\-trait hole. He saw Dean and Seamus sitting in a group nearby: This meant that the dormitory must be empty, or nearly so. Without\lang3081  \lang1033 speaking to anybody, without making eye contact at all, Harry walked straight across the room and through the door to the boys\rquote  dormitories.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As he had hoped, Ron was waiting for him, still fully dressed, sit\-ting on his bed. Harry sat down on his own four-poster and for a moment, they simply stared at each other.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They\rquote re talking about closing the school,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lupin said they would,\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a pause.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So?\rdblquote  said Ron in a very low voice, as though he thought the fur\-niture might be listening in. \ldblquote Did you find one? Did you get it? A \emdash  a Horcrux?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry shook his head. All that had taken place around that black lake seemed like an old nightmare now; had it really happened, and only hours ago?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You didn\rquote t get it?\rdblquote  said Ron, looking crestfallen. \ldblquote It wasn\rquote t there?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Someone had already taken it and left a fake in its place.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Already \i taken\i0  \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Wordlessly, Harry pulled the fake locket from his pocket, opened it, and passed it to Ron. The full story could wait. \'85 It did not matter tonight\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 nothing mattered except the end, the end of their pointless adventure, the end of Dumbledore\rquote s life. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote R.A.B.,\rdblquote  whispered Ron, \ldblquote but who was that?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry, lying back on his bed fully clothed and staring blankly upwards. He felt no curiosity at all about R.A.B.: He doubted that he would ever feel curious again. As he lay there,\lang3081  \lang1033 he became aware suddenly that the grounds were silent. Fawkes had stopped singing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he knew, without knowing how he knew it, that the phoenix had gone, had left Hogwarts for good, just as Dumbledore had left the school, had left the world \'85 had left Harry.\lang3081\par
